1
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:43,085
Long time no see, Okkotsu.

2
00:00:44,253 --> 00:00:46,338
Don't come over here.

3
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:50,008
Come on, don't be so cold.

4
00:00:50,008 --> 00:00:51,093
(I said don't.)

5
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:52,553
I said don't.

6
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:56,306
Do you know how much
I've wanted to beat you up?

7
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:59,768
Just imagine how I've felt.

8
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:00,811
(Stop it.)

9
00:01:00,811 --> 00:01:02,020
Stop it.

10
00:01:02,104 --> 00:01:04,690
If you keep tempting me like this,

11
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:06,817
I might kill you accidentally.

12
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,527
Don't come over here!

13
00:01:08,527 --> 00:01:09,528
Rika!

14
00:01:11,029 --> 00:01:12,155
Rika?

15
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:14,116
(Record: November 2016, Tokyo)

16
00:01:14,116 --> 00:01:15,492
(Reason: persistent bullying
by classmates)

17
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:16,952
(four male students injured seriously,
including the leader)

18
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:22,040
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:24,501
I'm sorry.

20
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:31,133
I'm sorry.

21
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:34,219
I'm sorry.

22
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:56,408
A completely secret execution?

23
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:58,118
No way.

24
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:01,413
But the boy already agreed.

25
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:06,543
He's only 16, still a minor.

26
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:09,671
If so, we won't even know
how many will be cursed to death.

27
00:02:10,339 --> 00:02:12,299
Currently, there are 3 Grade 2 sorcerers

28
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:15,344
and 1 Grade 1 sorcerer being hurt.

29
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,639
That's why you came to me.

30
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:22,392
Have you forgotten that?

31
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,395
So actually...

32
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:26,730
Yes.

33
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,398
Okkotsu Yuta

34
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,527
will be guarded by Jujutsu High.

35
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:36,990
What is this,

36
00:02:37,366 --> 00:02:38,825
Okkotsu Yuta?

37
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:42,579
It was a knife.

38
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:46,333
I tried to kill myself,

39
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,963
but Rika stopped me.

40
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:53,465
That's dark.

41
00:02:56,426 --> 00:02:58,512
You're going to a new school today.

42
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:00,764
I'm not going.

43
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:07,020
I don't want to hurt anyone anymore,

44
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:10,148
so I will just stay here.

45
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:12,818
But...

46
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:15,320
you will feel lonely in that case.

47
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,534
The curse placed upon you

48
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:23,036
can save people too,

49
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,289
(Tokyo Jujutsu High School)
depending on how it's used.

50
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,667
Learn to use that power properly.

51
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:31,461
It's not like it'll be too late

52
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,881
to cast everything away after that.

53
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:22,674
"JUJUTSU KAISEN"

54
00:06:29,139 --> 00:06:31,767
Did you hear that
the transfer student coming today

55
00:06:32,434 --> 00:06:35,729
has stuffed four
of his classmates into a locker?

56
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:36,813
He killed them?

57
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:37,773
Tuna mayo?

58
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:40,192
No, but seriously injured.

59
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:44,404
Anyway, if he's cocky,
I'll kick his ass.

60
00:06:44,863 --> 00:06:46,240
Fish flakes.

61
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:51,453
I'll introduce
the transfer student to you all!

62
00:06:51,453 --> 00:06:54,289
Everyone, get excited!

63
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:58,293
Be excited.

64
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:01,797
I heard he makes troubles.

65
00:07:02,506 --> 00:07:05,884
I'm not going to
welcome someone like that.

66
00:07:06,385 --> 00:07:07,219
Salmon.

67
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:13,016
Oh, well.

68
00:07:14,351 --> 00:07:16,311
Come on in!

69
00:07:16,562 --> 00:07:19,606
I can sense a damp mood even from here.

70
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:27,573
I'll ignore him.

71
00:07:44,548 --> 00:07:45,632
I'm Okkotsu Yut...

72
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:49,720
Is this some kind of test?

73
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,639
Hey.

74
00:07:54,183 --> 00:07:56,894
You're cursed?

75
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:59,730
This is a place to learn curses,

76
00:08:00,147 --> 00:08:02,816
not for the cursed one to be.

77
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:09,615
In Japan, over 10,000 people
die mysteriously

78
00:08:09,615 --> 00:08:12,284
or go missing on average every year.

79
00:08:12,743 --> 00:08:17,414
Most of them are casualties of curses

80
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:19,291
born from negative emotions of people.

81
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:22,753
Some of the cases
were caused by curse users.

82
00:08:23,253 --> 00:08:26,924
Only curses can affect other curses.

83
00:08:27,758 --> 00:08:31,178
We learn curses to exorcise curses here.

84
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:33,889
This is Tokyo Jujutsu High School.

85
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,393
Why didn't you tell me that beforehand?

86
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,564
He just told him that?

87
00:08:43,232 --> 00:08:44,525
Sorry.

88
00:08:45,526 --> 00:08:47,402
You'd better get away from him quickly.

89
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:56,495
Do not...

90
00:08:56,703 --> 00:08:58,497
Wait! Rika!

91
00:08:59,373 --> 00:09:02,835
...bully Yuta!

92
00:09:02,918 --> 00:09:04,461
(Special Grade Cursed Human:
Okkotsu Yuta)

93
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:05,921
(Special grade vengeful cursed spirit:
Orimoto Rika)

94
00:09:05,921 --> 00:09:08,924
(Record: Six Years Ago,
Sendai City, Miyagi Prefecture)

95
00:09:13,136 --> 00:09:15,472
-Over there!
-What is it?

96
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:20,310
Happy birthday, Yuta.

97
00:09:24,648 --> 00:09:27,192
Yay! Can I open it?

98
00:09:27,526 --> 00:09:28,569
Sure.

99
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:30,404
Can I open it?

100
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:31,947
I said OK.

101
00:09:38,203 --> 00:09:39,246
A ring?

102
00:09:39,955 --> 00:09:41,665
It's an engagement ring.

103
00:09:41,665 --> 00:09:42,749
Engagement?

104
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:56,847
It's a promise.

105
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:59,474
When we grow up,

106
00:09:59,474 --> 00:10:02,144
we'll get married.

107
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:08,275
No way!

108
00:10:09,985 --> 00:10:11,486
Hey! Call an ambulance!

109
00:10:11,486 --> 00:10:13,363
Idiot! Look at her!

110
00:10:13,989 --> 00:10:17,034
There's no way to save her!
Her head was totally crushed!

111
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:18,368
But still...

112
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,121
A child got run over by a car!

113
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:22,623
Yes! Hurry!

114
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:26,627
-Look!
-I can't go near that!

115
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:29,755
Rika...

116
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,842
Yuta.

117
00:10:42,434 --> 00:10:44,645
Yuta...

118
00:10:45,646 --> 00:10:49,024
When we grow up,

119
00:10:49,316 --> 00:10:52,778
we'll get married!

120
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:58,909
It's a promise.

121
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:01,161
So as you can see,

122
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:04,665
this is the boy cursed by Rika,
who loved him,

123
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:07,543
Okkotsu Yuta!

124
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:10,420
Be nice to him, everyone!

125
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:16,635
If you attack Yuta,
Rika's curse will activate.

126
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:19,596
Anyway, be careful, everyone.

127
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:22,224
Can't you say that earlier?

128
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,018
They are a little rebellious.

129
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,979
I'll introduce them quickly.

130
00:11:27,688 --> 00:11:30,357
This teacher seems very weird.

131
00:11:30,899 --> 00:11:33,569
This is the cursed tool user,
Zen'in Maki.

132
00:11:33,569 --> 00:11:36,530
She uses special tools
to exorcise curses.

133
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:40,158
This is the cursed speech user,
Inumaki Toge.

134
00:11:40,158 --> 00:11:43,495
He can only speak in rice ball ingredients,
so good luck with your talking to him.

135
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:44,496
Kelp.

136
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:45,831
This is Panda.

137
00:11:45,831 --> 00:11:48,458
I'm Panda. Nice to meet you.

138
00:11:48,834 --> 00:11:51,044
Well, that's all.

139
00:11:51,253 --> 00:11:53,964
He didn't mention a word about the one
I wanted to know the most!

140
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:58,302
Good, now there are four students
in the first grade!

141
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,889
Three humans and one animal.

142
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:04,349
For afternoon jujutsu practice,

143
00:12:04,975 --> 00:12:06,977
you'll be paired into two groups.

144
00:12:07,477 --> 00:12:09,188
Toge, Panda, you pair up.

145
00:12:09,188 --> 00:12:10,439
Let's do our best.

146
00:12:10,814 --> 00:12:12,774
Maki, Yuta, you pair up.

147
00:12:14,276 --> 00:12:15,777
She seems reluctant.

148
00:12:21,617 --> 00:12:22,951
U-Um,

149
00:12:23,285 --> 00:12:25,704
I-I hope we can work well together.

150
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:30,709
You were bullied, weren't you?

151
00:12:36,757 --> 00:12:38,175
Was I right?

152
00:12:38,175 --> 00:12:41,011
I can easily tell that.
Even I'd bully you.

153
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:43,388
Maybe it's because of your curse?

154
00:12:43,639 --> 00:12:47,017
You always want to
brand yourself as a good person.

155
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:48,393
It's sickening.

156
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:52,439
You're being protected.
Why always act like a victim?

157
00:12:52,856 --> 00:12:55,025
You've always been passive, haven't you?

158
00:12:56,443 --> 00:12:59,029
Jujutsu High isn't that easy

159
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:02,157
to get by without any goal.

160
00:13:04,159 --> 00:13:06,453
Maki! That's enough!

161
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:07,829
Fish flakes.

162
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:10,374
Okay, fine.

163
00:13:10,624 --> 00:13:12,209
Stop nagging me.

164
00:13:12,668 --> 00:13:14,044
Sorry about that.

165
00:13:14,044 --> 00:13:17,965
She always acts like
she understands everyone.

166
00:13:18,257 --> 00:13:19,508
It's OK.

167
00:13:20,342 --> 00:13:22,302
She's right.

168
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:29,184
Where are we?

169
00:13:29,184 --> 00:13:31,186
Just an ordinary elementary school.

170
00:13:31,979 --> 00:13:36,149
Some children have gone missing here.

171
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:37,776
Missing?!

172
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:40,404
It happens in places like this.

173
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:44,199
Probably a naturally-occurring curse.

174
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:48,245
You mean the kids
were kidnapped by a curse?

175
00:13:48,245 --> 00:13:50,914
Yes. Two so far.

176
00:13:51,164 --> 00:13:53,876
Curses tend to gather in places

177
00:13:54,168 --> 00:13:56,253
that many people have memories of.

178
00:13:57,671 --> 00:14:00,048
Schools, hospitals...

179
00:14:00,424 --> 00:14:04,845
People keep recalling the past
and negative emotions will arise.

180
00:14:05,596 --> 00:14:07,347
As the emotions build up,

181
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:10,017
curses will be born, like this time.

182
00:14:10,642 --> 00:14:13,645
Exorcise the curses and save the kids.

183
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:15,105
If they're dead, take the bodies back.

184
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:17,858
Dead?

185
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:22,779
Emerge from darkness,
blacker than darkness.

186
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:24,865
Purify the residuals, curses all gone.

187
00:14:30,204 --> 00:14:32,039
It's getting dark.

188
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:34,666
It's a Curtain,

189
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,461
a barrier that will draw out the curses

190
00:14:37,836 --> 00:14:40,214
and keep you from being seen by others.

191
00:14:42,007 --> 00:14:44,426
The Curtain is easy to undo from inside.

192
00:14:46,970 --> 00:14:48,972
Now, be careful

193
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:51,225
not to die.

194
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,018
Die?

195
00:14:53,227 --> 00:14:54,019
Teacher!

196
00:14:54,019 --> 00:14:55,437
Transfer student.

197
00:14:56,813 --> 00:14:59,233
Don't get distracted.

198
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:05,322
Put...

199
00:15:05,697 --> 00:15:06,907
me...

200
00:15:07,741 --> 00:15:08,825
on?

201
00:15:12,663 --> 00:15:13,872
Put me...

202
00:15:14,665 --> 00:15:15,457
on?

203
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:17,459
It's coming this way!

204
00:15:18,001 --> 00:15:19,461
W-What do we do?!

205
00:15:19,461 --> 00:15:20,712
Don't scream.

206
00:15:25,217 --> 00:15:26,552
Remember.

207
00:15:26,552 --> 00:15:28,136
The weaker the curses are,

208
00:15:28,303 --> 00:15:30,430
the more likely they'll group together.

209
00:15:35,894 --> 00:15:38,564
Of course, so are the humans.

210
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:40,774
Awesome!

211
00:15:41,942 --> 00:15:43,569
Just one blow...

212
00:15:44,987 --> 00:15:46,905
OK, let's move it.

213
00:15:47,698 --> 00:15:48,949
Where to?

214
00:15:49,199 --> 00:15:51,410
Inside, of course.

215
00:16:02,421 --> 00:16:05,048
Zen'in, aren't you scared?

216
00:16:05,215 --> 00:16:06,550
Don't call me by my last name.

217
00:16:06,842 --> 00:16:08,677
S-Sorry...

218
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:11,638
But it seems like
a lot of ghosts would be here.

219
00:16:12,890 --> 00:16:14,516
They are already here.

220
00:16:14,892 --> 00:16:16,602
There aren't many curses here,

221
00:16:16,602 --> 00:16:18,520
even though the Curtain's been drawn.

222
00:16:19,563 --> 00:16:20,272
No,

223
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:22,816
there're many, just not attacking.

224
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:27,613
Is it because he's here?

225
00:16:28,155 --> 00:16:29,448
Something just moved!

226
00:16:30,115 --> 00:16:30,824
Hey!

227
00:16:30,949 --> 00:16:31,867
Yes?!

228
00:16:32,451 --> 00:16:34,328
What grade are you in?

229
00:16:35,537 --> 00:16:36,663
Testing my English proficiency?

230
00:16:36,788 --> 00:16:40,083
Jujutsu sorcerers are ranked
from Grade 1 to 4.

231
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:43,587
But I just came to Jujutsu High.

232
00:16:44,463 --> 00:16:46,089
I don't think I have that.

233
00:16:46,423 --> 00:16:48,509
Forget it.

234
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,594
Show me your student ID.

235
00:16:50,594 --> 00:16:52,596
You got one from
that dumb blindfolded guy, right?

236
00:16:53,889 --> 00:16:55,599
Dumb blindfolded guy?

237
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:58,602
Yes, here you go.

238
00:16:59,144 --> 00:17:02,356
You joined with no prior experience,
so you're probably in Grade 4...

239
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:03,232
(Student ID, Okkotsu Yuta)

240
00:17:03,232 --> 00:17:04,816
Special Grade?!

241
00:17:05,275 --> 00:17:06,818
Special Grade

242
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:08,904
is above even Grade 1, isn't it?

243
00:17:08,904 --> 00:17:12,574
-Is this some kind of joke?
-Zen'in!

244
00:17:12,574 --> 00:17:13,951
Zen'in!

245
00:17:14,451 --> 00:17:15,869
Behind you.

246
00:17:29,675 --> 00:17:30,926
Darn it!

247
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:33,470
Way too damn big!

248
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:36,098
Try this!

249
00:17:43,689 --> 00:17:45,482
Thank you...

250
00:17:45,482 --> 00:17:49,820
Thank you for the meal!

251
00:17:52,072 --> 00:17:53,782
Darn it!

252
00:17:53,782 --> 00:17:55,325
I dropped my cursed tool!

253
00:17:55,325 --> 00:17:57,619
Let us out, jerk!

254
00:18:00,455 --> 00:18:01,748
Where are we?

255
00:18:01,999 --> 00:18:04,710
Inside the curse's stomach!

256
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:06,461
Don't pass out over this.

257
00:18:07,254 --> 00:18:08,797
You mean it ate us?!

258
00:18:09,339 --> 00:18:13,135
Right! You are supposed to be
protected by your curse, aren't you?

259
00:18:13,385 --> 00:18:17,055
Even I don't know
what makes Rika come out!

260
00:18:17,306 --> 00:18:19,141
But what do we do now?!

261
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:22,394
When it's time, Curtain will go away,
and someone will help us out.

262
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:26,148
This is embarrassing! Darn it!

263
00:18:26,481 --> 00:18:27,900
Help!

264
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:32,696
Please! He's about to die!

265
00:18:35,908 --> 00:18:39,244
You mean the kids
were kidnapped by a curse?

266
00:18:39,244 --> 00:18:41,955
Yes. Two so far.

267
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:45,083
Exorcise the curses and save the kids.

268
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,627
If they're dead, take the bodies back.

269
00:18:47,377 --> 00:18:49,880
Great. They're still alive.

270
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,507
No, it's not good.

271
00:18:51,965 --> 00:18:53,425
Look closer.

272
00:18:54,468 --> 00:18:57,679
The bigger one's been
affected by the curse too.

273
00:18:57,679 --> 00:19:00,057
Both of them could die at any minute.

274
00:19:01,225 --> 00:19:04,186
Oh, no... What do we do?!

275
00:19:04,394 --> 00:19:05,938
There's nothing we can do!

276
00:19:05,938 --> 00:19:07,940
We can only wait for help!

277
00:19:08,398 --> 00:19:12,945
Not everyone is immune
to curses like you!

278
00:19:14,571 --> 00:19:15,906
Zen'in?

279
00:19:18,033 --> 00:19:19,451
Zen'in?!

280
00:19:22,955 --> 00:19:25,040
What's this wound?

281
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:28,210
Are you cursed?

282
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:31,797
Is she going to die?

283
00:19:33,757 --> 00:19:36,677
Please, save us, big brother!

284
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:39,638
Please!

285
00:19:40,973 --> 00:19:44,643
Even if you keep begging me, I can't...

286
00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:46,144
Okkotsu!

287
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:52,109
Seriously, why did you
come to Jujutsu High?

288
00:19:54,194 --> 00:19:56,446
What do you want to do?
What do you want to get?

289
00:19:56,446 --> 00:19:57,781
What do you want to achieve?

290
00:19:59,283 --> 00:20:03,829
I... don't want anyone
to get hurt anymore.

291
00:20:04,621 --> 00:20:07,374
I tried to lock myself up and disappear.

292
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:11,545
But I was told
that I will feel lonely if I do that,

293
00:20:11,962 --> 00:20:13,088
and I couldn't argue.

294
00:20:16,216 --> 00:20:17,885
I want to interact with people!

295
00:20:19,469 --> 00:20:21,388
I want to be needed by others!

296
00:20:21,638 --> 00:20:25,809
I want the confidence to live!

297
00:20:27,686 --> 00:20:29,271
Then exorcise them.

298
00:20:31,273 --> 00:20:34,359
Exorcise curses over and over again!

299
00:20:35,485 --> 00:20:38,864
Confidence and friends
will come to you after that!

300
00:20:40,449 --> 00:20:45,871
That's what Jujutsu High is for!

301
00:20:57,299 --> 00:20:58,550
Rika.

302
00:21:00,052 --> 00:21:01,386
What?

303
00:21:03,514 --> 00:21:05,265
Lend me your power.

304
00:21:18,195 --> 00:21:20,614
Who are you?

305
00:21:29,122 --> 00:21:31,834
Be quiet!

306
00:21:35,254 --> 00:21:37,339
That's terrifying.

307
00:21:37,756 --> 00:21:42,553
This is the full form of Orimoto Rika,
special grade vengeful cursed spirit?

308
00:21:44,847 --> 00:21:46,306
So scary.

309
00:21:48,809 --> 00:21:50,310
So pretty!

310
00:21:51,270 --> 00:21:56,984
Rika likes pretty stuff.

311
00:22:04,908 --> 00:22:06,368
Everyone...

312
00:22:07,661 --> 00:22:09,371
Almost there!

313
00:22:10,497 --> 00:22:13,041
I need to take you all
to the teacher for treatment,

314
00:22:13,584 --> 00:22:16,295
while Rika's distracting the curses!

315
00:22:26,388 --> 00:22:28,640
I can't collapse yet!

316
00:22:29,725 --> 00:22:31,101
Not yet!

317
00:22:35,814 --> 00:22:37,900
I just decided to change,

318
00:22:39,276 --> 00:22:40,944
here and now!

319
00:22:43,488 --> 00:22:44,990
You can do it,

320
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:47,826
Yuta.

321
00:22:52,623 --> 00:22:54,041
Yeah, I will!

322
00:22:59,171 --> 00:23:00,422
Welcome back.

323
00:23:01,632 --> 00:23:03,050
You did well.

324
00:23:10,224 --> 00:23:13,185
Both Maki and the kids are fine.

325
00:23:14,061 --> 00:23:15,562
Thank goodness.

326
00:23:16,438 --> 00:23:18,690
You don't look very satisfied.

327
00:23:20,484 --> 00:23:24,321
It was the first time
for me to let Rika out myself.

328
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,324
Really? That's a step forward.

329
00:24:12,703 --> 00:24:14,580
Here we go!

330
00:24:16,748 --> 00:24:18,792
Stop, Yuta!

331
00:24:20,419 --> 00:24:22,045
I said stop!

332
00:24:26,341 --> 00:24:28,677
Stop, Rika!

333
00:24:28,677 --> 00:24:29,970
There! Take that!

334
00:24:38,937 --> 00:24:40,522
It's a promise.

335
00:24:40,522 --> 00:24:43,984
When we grow up, we'll get married.

336
00:24:45,235 --> 00:24:46,361
Sure!

337
00:24:51,283 --> 00:24:57,164
Then we'll be together forever and ever!

338
00:25:00,042 --> 00:25:01,502
What's wrong?

339
00:25:02,127 --> 00:25:03,629
Nothing.

340
00:25:03,962 --> 00:25:06,798
Just something came to my mind.

341
00:25:07,758 --> 00:25:10,385
Maybe it's not Rika who cursed me.

342
00:25:11,553 --> 00:25:14,806
I might have cursed Rika.

343
00:25:17,142 --> 00:25:19,144
This is only my personal theory,

344
00:25:19,311 --> 00:25:21,396
but there's no curse
more twisted than love.

345
00:25:28,779 --> 00:25:30,155
Teacher.

346
00:25:30,989 --> 00:25:34,326
While I'm at Jujutsu High,

347
00:25:35,577 --> 00:25:37,579
my goal is to break Rika's curse.

348
00:25:58,350 --> 00:26:01,728
Special grade vengeful cursed spirit,
Orimoto Rika,

349
00:26:01,728 --> 00:26:04,648
was fully manifested within 422 seconds.

350
00:26:05,148 --> 00:26:09,987
We entrusted Okkotsu to you
just to prevent this sort of thing.

351
00:26:09,987 --> 00:26:12,155
There's no room for excuses,

352
00:26:12,155 --> 00:26:13,824
Gojo Satoru.

353
00:26:14,116 --> 00:26:17,786
I wasn't going to make any excuses.

354
00:26:17,786 --> 00:26:19,454
How can you joke about this?

355
00:26:19,788 --> 00:26:22,207
If Orimoto Rika lost control,

356
00:26:22,207 --> 00:26:24,668
it could have wiped out the entire town!

357
00:26:25,169 --> 00:26:27,671
I would have risked my life to stop it.

358
00:26:28,422 --> 00:26:29,590
Listen,

359
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:32,676
there's only one thing
we're sure about that curse:

360
00:26:33,594 --> 00:26:34,970
Unknown.

361
00:26:35,512 --> 00:26:38,682
How could a little girl who was not from
a family of past jujutsu sorcerers

362
00:26:38,682 --> 00:26:42,477
become such an immense curse?

363
00:26:42,895 --> 00:26:46,773
We can't control something
we don't understand.

364
00:26:47,441 --> 00:26:50,110
So it'll take trial and error.

365
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:52,321
Just stay out of it.

366
00:26:53,071 --> 00:26:57,576
Do not forget. Okkotsu's
secret execution was only suspended.

367
00:26:58,327 --> 00:26:59,828
And don't you forget

368
00:27:00,704 --> 00:27:05,250
that if it comes to that,
I'll side with Okkotsu.

369
00:27:09,338 --> 00:27:10,422
Christ,

370
00:27:10,422 --> 00:27:12,424
rude geezers.

371
00:27:13,258 --> 00:27:15,302
I don't want to
become someone like them.

372
00:27:15,636 --> 00:27:17,804
I'll have to be careful.

373
00:27:18,263 --> 00:27:19,973
After all,

374
00:27:19,973 --> 00:27:24,770
no one's allowed to
take youth away from young people.

375
00:27:31,235 --> 00:27:33,820
Maki, Toge, last lap.

376
00:27:37,032 --> 00:27:39,034
No one is.

377
00:27:49,127 --> 00:27:50,921
Come, go ahead.

378
00:27:51,296 --> 00:27:52,714
OK.

379
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:08,272
It's nearly impossible
to exorcise a curse

380
00:28:08,272 --> 00:28:09,982
as immense as Orimoto Rika.

381
00:28:09,982 --> 00:28:12,526
But breaking it is a different story.

382
00:28:13,277 --> 00:28:16,405
You have to read thousands of
knots of the cursed energy,

383
00:28:16,405 --> 00:28:18,740
and unravel them one by one.

384
00:28:19,533 --> 00:28:23,745
Only you are suitable for this method,
because you are cursed.

385
00:28:23,996 --> 00:28:25,914
What exactly shall I do?

386
00:28:25,914 --> 00:28:27,416
Use this.

387
00:28:31,003 --> 00:28:32,337
A katana?

388
00:28:32,337 --> 00:28:35,841
Curses are most stable
when they're possessing some object.

389
00:28:36,508 --> 00:28:40,846
Back then, you were connected to
Orimoto Rika by that ring.

390
00:28:41,138 --> 00:28:42,848
A pipeline's already there.

391
00:28:43,557 --> 00:28:45,475
So now you need to
borrow part of Rika's curse,

392
00:28:45,475 --> 00:28:47,644
imbue it into the katana,
and control it.

393
00:28:48,478 --> 00:28:50,397
Increase the amount as you repeat it,

394
00:28:50,397 --> 00:28:53,066
and eventually you'll have
all of it under your control.

395
00:28:53,942 --> 00:28:56,361
Then you will be free.

396
00:28:57,571 --> 00:29:00,115
Both you and her.

397
00:29:01,283 --> 00:29:04,077
Imbue the curse into the katana...

398
00:29:04,077 --> 00:29:05,913
In addition,

399
00:29:05,913 --> 00:29:08,373
you need to learn how to use the katana.

400
00:29:09,166 --> 00:29:12,461
You're too weak.

401
00:29:12,711 --> 00:29:15,297
We'll have to train you thoroughly.

402
00:29:47,496 --> 00:29:48,413
Tuna.

403
00:30:06,723 --> 00:30:09,726
Everyone, how's it going?

404
00:30:10,727 --> 00:30:11,854
Uh...

405
00:30:12,771 --> 00:30:14,690
Don't get distracted.

406
00:30:15,482 --> 00:30:16,316
Yes.

407
00:30:16,316 --> 00:30:18,110
Take your stance, idiot!

408
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,528
So ruthless!

409
00:30:19,945 --> 00:30:20,654
Yes!

410
00:30:21,738 --> 00:30:24,157
You're going to
land a blow on me, aren't you?

411
00:30:26,994 --> 00:30:28,161
Yes!

412
00:30:43,385 --> 00:30:44,761
She dodged that?!

413
00:30:45,387 --> 00:30:46,722
But she's off-balance!

414
00:30:46,722 --> 00:30:48,932
I'll get her on the landing!

415
00:30:51,351 --> 00:30:52,102
No way!

416
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,733
There, you're dead.

417
00:30:58,275 --> 00:31:00,235
I win again.

418
00:31:00,777 --> 00:31:02,738
Was that last part necessary?

419
00:31:02,988 --> 00:31:04,406
Don't be soft.

420
00:31:04,615 --> 00:31:06,909
You should always treat it
like it's a real battle.

421
00:31:07,534 --> 00:31:11,914
Punishment can speed up your growth.

422
00:31:13,624 --> 00:31:15,751
That's right. I'm...

423
00:31:17,002 --> 00:31:20,881
One more, please!

424
00:31:21,965 --> 00:31:25,761
I want to break Rika's curse!

425
00:31:28,805 --> 00:31:31,725
It's been three months
since Yuta came to Jujutsu High.

426
00:31:32,184 --> 00:31:34,311
His moves are much better now.

427
00:31:34,311 --> 00:31:35,145
Salmon.

428
00:31:35,145 --> 00:31:37,856
He is more positive too.

429
00:31:37,856 --> 00:31:38,732
Salmon roe.

430
00:31:39,233 --> 00:31:41,818
Maki looks like having fun too.

431
00:31:42,069 --> 00:31:45,405
In the past, she seldom got anyone
to fight with using a tool...

432
00:31:47,491 --> 00:31:48,992
Revelation!

433
00:31:49,409 --> 00:31:52,079
Yuta, come here!

434
00:31:52,079 --> 00:31:53,956
COME ON!

435
00:31:54,915 --> 00:31:56,667
What's up, Panda?

436
00:31:56,667 --> 00:31:59,753
A very important thing! Listen closely!

437
00:32:00,337 --> 00:32:03,674
Do you prefer big boobs or small boobs?

438
00:32:03,674 --> 00:32:04,758
You serious?

439
00:32:05,717 --> 00:32:07,886
I've never really given it much thought.

440
00:32:07,886 --> 00:32:09,304
(Sexy Talk)

441
00:32:09,304 --> 00:32:12,140
I suppose I prefer them somewhat big,
as most people do.

442
00:32:14,518 --> 00:32:15,811
Maki!

443
00:32:17,229 --> 00:32:19,231
You've got a chance!

444
00:32:19,231 --> 00:32:22,401
Chance!

445
00:32:23,026 --> 00:32:25,070
What are you talking about?
I'll kill you!

446
00:32:25,070 --> 00:32:26,864
Don't be shy! You're not a pupil.

447
00:32:26,864 --> 00:32:28,365
OK, I'm going to kill you!

448
00:32:28,365 --> 00:32:30,200
I don't give a damn about CITES!

449
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,869
What's that about?

450
00:32:32,327 --> 00:32:33,787
Kelp.

451
00:32:38,083 --> 00:32:41,295
I still don't really get Inumaki,

452
00:32:41,795 --> 00:32:43,922
so he seems a little scary sometimes.

453
00:32:45,257 --> 00:32:48,385
Okay, gather round!

454
00:32:48,844 --> 00:32:52,097
You two, go on with your training.

455
00:32:52,931 --> 00:32:54,558
Toge, you are requested by someone.

456
00:32:54,558 --> 00:32:56,518
It's a curse you're perfect for.

457
00:32:56,518 --> 00:32:58,270
Exorcise it quickly.

458
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,438
Salmon.

459
00:32:59,438 --> 00:33:00,898
Requested?

460
00:33:00,898 --> 00:33:03,400
Toge's the only Grade 2 sorcerer
in the first grade.

461
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:05,986
He's allowed to
complete missions on his own.

462
00:33:06,778 --> 00:33:08,113
That's awesome.

463
00:33:08,113 --> 00:33:09,364
You're a Special Grade.

464
00:33:09,823 --> 00:33:11,825
You go with him, Yuta.

465
00:33:11,825 --> 00:33:13,118
To be Toge's support.

466
00:33:14,244 --> 00:33:15,704
Support?

467
00:33:15,704 --> 00:33:18,123
More like an observer, really.

468
00:33:19,124 --> 00:33:21,168
There are many kinds of jujutsu.

469
00:33:21,168 --> 00:33:24,796
Different sorcerers may have
different ways to exorcise a curse.

470
00:33:25,547 --> 00:33:28,300
Toge's cursed speech is a good example.

471
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:30,135
Make sure to learn from him.

472
00:33:30,427 --> 00:33:31,512
Cursed speech?

473
00:33:31,512 --> 00:33:32,679
Literally,

474
00:33:32,679 --> 00:33:34,389
it's to imbue speech with curses.

475
00:33:34,723 --> 00:33:36,892
It'll make sense to you
once you see it with your own eyes.

476
00:33:37,351 --> 00:33:40,938
To break a curse,
you must understand the curse first.

477
00:33:42,439 --> 00:33:44,358
My first real mission...

478
00:33:44,358 --> 00:33:45,817
No, the second one?

479
00:33:45,817 --> 00:33:48,237
I'm so nervous!

480
00:33:50,030 --> 00:33:51,198
Salmon.

481
00:33:53,575 --> 00:33:55,661
I-I'm sorry.

482
00:33:56,703 --> 00:33:58,163
Yuta, one second.

483
00:33:59,039 --> 00:34:00,290
Yes?

484
00:34:00,457 --> 00:34:03,710
Sorry, I won't be able to
go with you this time.

485
00:34:03,710 --> 00:34:07,005
But since the job could be handled
by Toge on his own,

486
00:34:07,005 --> 00:34:08,382
you can take it easy.

487
00:34:08,590 --> 00:34:11,134
Just remember one thing.

488
00:34:12,344 --> 00:34:13,804
Don't let Rika out.

489
00:34:15,430 --> 00:34:18,851
There's no guarantee
that she can go back as last time.

490
00:34:19,226 --> 00:34:20,727
Only use the part of Rika's power

491
00:34:20,727 --> 00:34:23,146
that you can imbue into your katana.

492
00:34:24,356 --> 00:34:27,150
If you let her out fully again...

493
00:34:27,150 --> 00:34:28,402
What then?

494
00:34:29,611 --> 00:34:32,406
You and I will both be killed!

495
00:34:32,781 --> 00:34:34,074
Counting on you.

496
00:34:34,408 --> 00:34:35,409
Wh...

497
00:34:36,034 --> 00:34:40,163
Why does he have to add
the last sentence at this moment?

498
00:34:57,389 --> 00:34:58,432
We've here.

499
00:35:00,517 --> 00:35:02,311
Hapina Shopping Center.

500
00:35:02,311 --> 00:35:05,439
Now, most of the stores here are closed.

501
00:35:05,439 --> 00:35:06,023
(We're closed.)

502
00:35:06,023 --> 00:35:07,983
The entire area will be demolished

503
00:35:07,983 --> 00:35:11,570
to attract a shopping mall to be built.

504
00:35:13,906 --> 00:35:18,118
During an inspection of the area,
we confirmed a pack of low-level curses.

505
00:35:18,577 --> 00:35:22,706
We'd like Grade 2 sorcerer,
Inumaki, to exorcise them.

506
00:35:23,081 --> 00:35:25,459
Where's sorcerer Inumaki?

507
00:35:26,084 --> 00:35:26,960
Disappeared?

508
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,420
Thank you.

509
00:35:28,837 --> 00:35:30,380
Oh, Mr. Ijichi, over there.

510
00:35:32,883 --> 00:35:34,134
He went for shopping?

511
00:35:34,843 --> 00:35:36,303
What did you buy?

512
00:35:39,097 --> 00:35:40,641
Throat medicine?

513
00:35:41,850 --> 00:35:44,436
Anyway, it would cause troubles

514
00:35:44,436 --> 00:35:47,022
if the building
they're spending money on is haunted,

515
00:35:47,022 --> 00:35:49,775
so they want us
to exorcise the curses now.

516
00:35:49,775 --> 00:35:50,651
Salmon.

517
00:35:51,443 --> 00:35:53,946
Now, I'll draw the Curtain.

518
00:35:54,655 --> 00:35:55,822
Good luck.

519
00:36:07,251 --> 00:36:10,462
He said it was
a pack of low-level curses.

520
00:36:10,462 --> 00:36:11,755
Spiced cod roe.

521
00:36:28,772 --> 00:36:30,816
That's not fair, Mama.

522
00:36:31,233 --> 00:36:33,318
My big brother got more.

523
00:36:34,236 --> 00:36:36,321
So what? Let's trade.

524
00:36:36,488 --> 00:36:38,824
I want to eat sushi!

525
00:36:48,250 --> 00:36:50,878
The weaker the curses are,
the more likely they'll group together.

526
00:36:51,587 --> 00:36:55,382
Even so, there are too many of them!

527
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:02,806
Inumaki?

528
00:37:04,474 --> 00:37:06,268
It's dangerous if you get that close.

529
00:37:06,268 --> 00:37:07,519
Explode.

530
00:37:14,693 --> 00:37:17,362
This is the cursed speech?

531
00:37:19,323 --> 00:37:20,866
It's over already?

532
00:37:22,242 --> 00:37:23,785
Tuna mayo.

533
00:37:23,785 --> 00:37:25,370
His voice is really worn out!

534
00:37:26,705 --> 00:37:28,874
No wonder he bought throat medicine.

535
00:37:30,918 --> 00:37:32,878
That's an incredible power,

536
00:37:33,253 --> 00:37:35,589
but it comes with
a good deal of risk too.

537
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,345
Fish flakes.

538
00:37:41,345 --> 00:37:42,387
What's wrong?

539
00:37:42,888 --> 00:37:44,473
Right.

540
00:37:44,473 --> 00:37:46,058
The Curtain hasn't been lifted.

541
00:37:47,768 --> 00:37:48,810
Huh?

542
00:37:49,561 --> 00:37:51,230
We won't be able to get out.

543
00:37:59,321 --> 00:38:01,281
What is this curse?

544
00:38:01,281 --> 00:38:03,325
Nothing like the ones from before.

545
00:38:03,784 --> 00:38:04,910
ZOMBA

546
00:38:08,288 --> 00:38:09,623
Inumaki!

547
00:38:10,707 --> 00:38:11,667
Twist!

548
00:38:24,096 --> 00:38:26,348
What?! What is that?!

549
00:38:32,437 --> 00:38:35,023
He said they'd be low-level!

550
00:38:35,023 --> 00:38:37,192
Much more powerful.

551
00:38:37,484 --> 00:38:38,777
Smaller in size,

552
00:38:40,279 --> 00:38:43,407
but much scarier than the big ones

553
00:38:43,949 --> 00:38:45,367
from that elementary school.

554
00:38:46,410 --> 00:38:48,829
Oh, Inumaki, you're hurt.

555
00:38:49,037 --> 00:38:50,581
Is your finger all right?

556
00:38:50,998 --> 00:38:52,791
That looks painful.

557
00:38:53,083 --> 00:38:54,209
Salmon.

558
00:38:55,002 --> 00:38:57,087
You shouldn't mess with it!

559
00:38:58,881 --> 00:39:00,048
Sorry.

560
00:39:00,841 --> 00:39:01,967
It's my fault.

561
00:39:10,851 --> 00:39:13,770
It's not pursuing us
or searching for us.

562
00:39:14,771 --> 00:39:16,607
I'll contact Mr. Ijichi.

563
00:39:17,900 --> 00:39:19,276
No signal?

564
00:39:19,651 --> 00:39:20,903
Why?

565
00:39:21,069 --> 00:39:22,404
Fish flakes.

566
00:39:24,072 --> 00:39:25,699
Because of the Curtain?

567
00:39:27,910 --> 00:39:29,369
If the Curtain won't lift,

568
00:39:29,369 --> 00:39:31,788
then we have to exorcise it, right?

569
00:39:36,543 --> 00:39:37,961
Inumaki?

570
00:39:38,545 --> 00:39:40,422
Should you be moving around already?

571
00:39:42,174 --> 00:39:43,467
Kelp.

572
00:39:47,471 --> 00:39:49,598
You're going alone?

573
00:40:14,581 --> 00:40:16,834
Thank you, Inumaki.

574
00:40:20,254 --> 00:40:22,047
But I'm all right.

575
00:40:28,637 --> 00:40:30,264
Let's do our best together!

576
00:40:43,527 --> 00:40:46,446
Kill him, Yuta!

577
00:40:51,869 --> 00:40:53,704
Mad? Why?

578
00:40:53,704 --> 00:40:55,539
It was already scary enough!

579
00:41:02,171 --> 00:41:03,547
Don't take your eyes off him.

580
00:41:03,881 --> 00:41:05,382
Don't stop moving.

581
00:41:06,300 --> 00:41:08,552
Imbue the curse into the katana.

582
00:41:25,736 --> 00:41:27,988
Inumaki is so kind.

583
00:41:28,530 --> 00:41:30,908
He doesn't want to
accidentally curse others,

584
00:41:30,908 --> 00:41:34,203
so he speaks in rice ball ingredients
that can't carry curses.

585
00:41:34,286 --> 00:41:36,038
Even today, he helped me out.

586
00:41:36,413 --> 00:41:38,624
He tried to keep me away from danger.

587
00:41:40,042 --> 00:41:41,126
Even back then,

588
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:45,631
he was showing consideration
for my anxiety.

589
00:41:52,304 --> 00:41:53,388
ZOZO

590
00:41:55,766 --> 00:41:56,850
ZORA

591
00:41:56,975 --> 00:41:57,851
That was shallow!

592
00:41:57,851 --> 00:41:59,353
No. He's too tough!

593
00:42:02,564 --> 00:42:05,317
I still can't compete with this curse,

594
00:42:06,026 --> 00:42:06,944
but...

595
00:42:10,447 --> 00:42:11,865
Inumaki!

596
00:42:13,825 --> 00:42:16,036
I'll make sure...

597
00:42:16,411 --> 00:42:17,746
to respond...

598
00:42:18,413 --> 00:42:19,998
to Inumaki's kindness!

599
00:42:35,722 --> 00:42:37,140
Get crushed!

600
00:42:38,934 --> 00:42:40,185
BA...

601
00:42:44,398 --> 00:42:45,941
Awesome!

602
00:42:46,066 --> 00:42:47,442
Leaf mustard.

603
00:42:50,028 --> 00:42:51,488
I'm fine.

604
00:42:51,488 --> 00:42:53,031
Only a scratch.

605
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:56,618
Salmon.

606
00:43:00,289 --> 00:43:01,623
Good work!

607
00:43:04,835 --> 00:43:06,628
Once I break Rika's curse,

608
00:43:07,212 --> 00:43:09,506
I'll be a normal person.

609
00:43:10,883 --> 00:43:13,260
I won't be able to
stay at Jujutsu High anymore.

610
00:43:13,927 --> 00:43:16,013
But until then,

611
00:43:16,346 --> 00:43:18,432
I want to be helpful to everyone.

612
00:43:20,601 --> 00:43:22,394
What do we do about the Curtain?

613
00:43:23,896 --> 00:43:25,022
What a shame.

614
00:43:25,772 --> 00:43:28,525
I came here to see this rumored Rika.

615
00:43:29,026 --> 00:43:30,777
As a fellow Special Grade,

616
00:43:30,777 --> 00:43:32,821
I was hoping to meet him soon.

617
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:37,576
I need to give back
the thing he dropped.

618
00:43:47,628 --> 00:43:49,546
Toge's cursed speech

619
00:43:50,047 --> 00:43:52,466
is something he was born with,

620
00:43:52,466 --> 00:43:54,885
so back in the days,
he suffered quite a bit.

621
00:43:55,552 --> 00:43:59,014
Sometimes, he cursed people
he never intended to curse.

622
00:43:59,139 --> 00:44:02,226
His situation was rather
similar to yours.

623
00:44:02,851 --> 00:44:07,147
That's why he's been caring about you
since you were transferred here.

624
00:44:08,148 --> 00:44:11,485
He's a good guy,
though he might be easily misunderstood.

625
00:44:12,611 --> 00:44:14,863
I hope you can get along with him.

626
00:44:16,198 --> 00:44:18,700
-Yeah, I'll...
-Come on, let's start morning training!

627
00:44:19,117 --> 00:44:20,410
Oh, right.

628
00:44:20,410 --> 00:44:22,079
Panda! What are you laughing about?!

629
00:44:22,287 --> 00:44:23,580
I'll kill you!

630
00:44:24,164 --> 00:44:26,708
-It's nothing.
-Maki...

631
00:44:27,876 --> 00:44:30,045
I'd like to imbue my curse

632
00:44:30,254 --> 00:44:33,215
into my katana more smoothly.
Do you know any tricks?

633
00:44:33,215 --> 00:44:34,341
Nope.

634
00:44:34,716 --> 00:44:36,969
Don't ask me about cursed energy.

635
00:44:44,226 --> 00:44:46,979
I searched every inch of
the shopping center,

636
00:44:46,979 --> 00:44:49,648
and found three
different kinds of residuals.

637
00:44:50,065 --> 00:44:54,653
Even Mr. Ijichi said we are not likely
to find anything more than that.

638
00:44:54,653 --> 00:44:56,947
Got it. Thanks.

639
00:44:56,947 --> 00:44:57,739
My pleasure!

640
00:45:30,230 --> 00:45:31,857
My apologies.

641
00:45:32,399 --> 00:45:36,403
After inspection, we found
someone placed a second Curtain

642
00:45:36,403 --> 00:45:39,781
on top of mine.

643
00:45:39,781 --> 00:45:40,782
In addition,

644
00:45:41,116 --> 00:45:45,037
a semi-Grade 1 curse
showed up unexpectedly.

645
00:45:45,454 --> 00:45:48,373
It's my fault
for not being more thorough.

646
00:45:48,624 --> 00:45:50,083
I'll accept any punishment.

647
00:45:50,083 --> 00:45:52,878
It's fine. You were just outclassed.

648
00:45:53,086 --> 00:45:54,546
You mean...

649
00:45:55,589 --> 00:45:57,549
You've already got an idea
about who did it?

650
00:46:13,440 --> 00:46:15,067
Geto Suguru,

651
00:46:16,735 --> 00:46:19,071
one of the four
Special Grade jujutsu sorcerers,

652
00:46:19,863 --> 00:46:22,574
who was banished from Jujutsu High

653
00:46:23,325 --> 00:46:26,078
after cursing over
a hundred normal people to death.

654
00:46:26,495 --> 00:46:28,580
He's the worst curse user.

655
00:46:42,010 --> 00:46:44,513
It's fine. Let's just go home.

656
00:46:44,513 --> 00:46:48,225
It's all right.
Just wait a little longer.

657
00:46:48,225 --> 00:46:49,309
But...

658
00:47:05,033 --> 00:47:10,163
So, you said your daughter
was being haunted by a ghost.

659
00:47:10,706 --> 00:47:12,916
Is that so, Ms. Sato?

660
00:47:13,125 --> 00:47:15,043
Yes... um...

661
00:47:15,043 --> 00:47:16,545
actually, it's Saito.

662
00:47:17,129 --> 00:47:19,673
No, you are Sato.

663
00:47:19,673 --> 00:47:22,551
That's what I've decided.
Sato is better.

664
00:47:25,929 --> 00:47:27,806
Mom, let's go home.

665
00:47:27,806 --> 00:47:31,602
But you haven't been
sleeping well lately, right?

666
00:47:31,602 --> 00:47:33,103
Even so, in a place so suspicious...

667
00:47:33,103 --> 00:47:36,190
You constantly feel
someone is staring at you.

668
00:47:37,482 --> 00:47:41,111
You feel heavy on shoulders,
and hard to breathe sometimes,

669
00:47:41,737 --> 00:47:44,406
as if you forgot how to breathe.

670
00:47:45,532 --> 00:47:47,201
And

671
00:47:47,492 --> 00:47:49,661
you often dream of being raped.

672
00:47:50,454 --> 00:47:51,914
How did you know?

673
00:47:54,208 --> 00:47:55,209
Don't move.

674
00:48:07,471 --> 00:48:08,514
No way...

675
00:48:08,514 --> 00:48:10,182
I feel much better!

676
00:48:12,893 --> 00:48:16,605
Really appreciate what you did for me.

677
00:48:17,105 --> 00:48:20,609
My pleasure. We should all
help the people in need.

678
00:48:20,817 --> 00:48:22,611
You can come to me anytime you need me.

679
00:48:24,530 --> 00:48:28,784
See, I told you he would be like a god!

680
00:48:30,118 --> 00:48:31,745
God?

681
00:48:32,120 --> 00:48:34,164
You're smart.

682
00:48:35,958 --> 00:48:38,544
Filthy monkeys
who can't even use jujutsu.

683
00:48:38,627 --> 00:48:41,046
You are showing
your true feelings, Mr. Geto.

684
00:48:41,296 --> 00:48:44,424
The leaders are all here.
Please go to the meeting room.

685
00:48:46,176 --> 00:48:48,303
What are you doing?

686
00:48:48,303 --> 00:48:50,097
Disinfecting and deodorizing.

687
00:48:50,264 --> 00:48:52,891
I don't want them
to catch the monkey smell.

688
00:48:54,226 --> 00:48:55,811
So happy.

689
00:48:56,228 --> 00:48:59,147
How long has it been
since we all gathered last time?

690
00:48:59,523 --> 00:49:02,901
Let's take a photo since we're all here.

691
00:49:02,901 --> 00:49:04,736
-Where is my camera?
-I have it.

692
00:49:07,614 --> 00:49:10,534
Geto! Give me Geto!

693
00:49:12,035 --> 00:49:13,495
Geto! Damn you!

694
00:49:14,288 --> 00:49:16,164
Oh, Mr. Kanamori.

695
00:49:16,456 --> 00:49:18,500
What brings you here in such a panic?

696
00:49:18,500 --> 00:49:21,920
Don't play dumb!
Hurry up and exorcise my curse!

697
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:24,840
Do you know how much I've paid you?

698
00:49:25,048 --> 00:49:26,049
How much?

699
00:49:26,049 --> 00:49:28,760
About one hundred and five million yen.

700
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:31,513
But none for the past six months.

701
00:49:31,513 --> 00:49:33,932
-Well...
-I guess that's it for you.

702
00:49:33,932 --> 00:49:35,517
What are you...?

703
00:49:39,229 --> 00:49:42,274
All monkeys have their own roles.

704
00:49:43,233 --> 00:49:45,194
There are money-collecting monkeys

705
00:49:45,194 --> 00:49:47,237
and curse-collecting monkeys.

706
00:49:47,446 --> 00:49:49,198
You're the former.

707
00:49:49,531 --> 00:49:52,034
Without money, you are useless.

708
00:49:55,621 --> 00:49:57,581
Screw you!

709
00:50:12,304 --> 00:50:13,889
Disgusting.

710
00:50:13,889 --> 00:50:16,225
Is he still a human?

711
00:50:16,558 --> 00:50:18,310
That's why I always say

712
00:50:18,310 --> 00:50:20,020
they're monkeys.

713
00:50:21,522 --> 00:50:23,899
It's time, my family.

714
00:50:23,982 --> 00:50:26,693
The age of monkeys is about to end.

715
00:50:26,902 --> 00:50:29,238
Let's build a paradise
for jujutsu sorcerers.

716
00:50:29,947 --> 00:50:32,491
First,

717
00:50:32,491 --> 00:50:36,119
we must smash the cornerstone
of the jujutsu world,

718
00:50:36,411 --> 00:50:37,788
Jujutsu High.

719
00:50:39,414 --> 00:50:40,707
What's wrong, Yuta?

720
00:50:40,707 --> 00:50:42,125
Well...

721
00:50:42,125 --> 00:50:44,127
I just had a bad feeling.

722
00:50:44,586 --> 00:50:45,629
You worry too much.

723
00:50:45,629 --> 00:50:46,839
Yes, too much.

724
00:50:46,839 --> 00:50:48,090
Fish flakes.

725
00:50:49,049 --> 00:50:50,843
Guys, wait for me.

726
00:50:51,134 --> 00:50:53,554
Your ability to sense
the cursed energy is not high.

727
00:50:53,554 --> 00:50:57,015
You must have become dulled
with Rika around.

728
00:50:57,015 --> 00:50:58,183
Tuna.

729
00:51:00,185 --> 00:51:03,105
We still don't know what Geto is up to.

730
00:51:03,230 --> 00:51:05,899
You're worrying too much.

731
00:51:05,899 --> 00:51:09,403
Principal, I don't think
that is possible.

732
00:51:09,403 --> 00:51:11,572
I confirmed it myself on the scene.

733
00:51:12,114 --> 00:51:16,243
I won't be wrong about
the residuals of Suguru's cursed energy.

734
00:51:18,161 --> 00:51:19,538
Suguru...

735
00:51:20,622 --> 00:51:21,790
GOD DAMN!

736
00:51:22,291 --> 00:51:23,959
Speak of the devil!

737
00:51:23,959 --> 00:51:28,422
Gather all semi-Grade 1 and above
sorcerers to the school gate in circle!

738
00:51:30,299 --> 00:51:31,967
That's unusual.

739
00:51:31,967 --> 00:51:33,969
Yuta's intuition was correct.

740
00:51:33,969 --> 00:51:35,095
Salmon.

741
00:51:44,229 --> 00:51:47,232
You're not school staff.

742
00:51:47,274 --> 00:51:49,067
I haven't seen that curse before.

743
00:51:49,067 --> 00:51:50,444
Salmon roe.

744
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:52,404
Such a big bird!

745
00:51:53,071 --> 00:51:55,365
This place never changes.

746
00:51:56,700 --> 00:51:59,703
Mr. Geto, is this really Tokyo?

747
00:52:00,037 --> 00:52:01,622
Feels like rural places.

748
00:52:01,622 --> 00:52:03,498
Nanako, that's rude.

749
00:52:03,498 --> 00:52:06,210
But you think so too, Mimiko, right?

750
00:52:06,376 --> 00:52:08,795
Enough! Get off!

751
00:52:08,795 --> 00:52:10,088
Aren't you cold?

752
00:52:10,088 --> 00:52:11,215
Who are they?

753
00:52:11,215 --> 00:52:14,468
It's a panda! So cute!

754
00:52:14,927 --> 00:52:16,595
Who are you people?

755
00:52:16,595 --> 00:52:19,139
Mr. Yuta won't allow intruders here.

756
00:52:19,139 --> 00:52:20,224
Kelp!

757
00:52:20,807 --> 00:52:24,102
Go home before you
get beaten by Mr. Yuta!

758
00:52:26,063 --> 00:52:28,106
Nice to meet you, Okkotsu.

759
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:30,108
I'm Geto Suguru.

760
00:52:30,359 --> 00:52:31,652
He's fast!

761
00:52:33,487 --> 00:52:34,947
Nice to meet you.

762
00:52:34,947 --> 00:52:37,991
You have truly wonderful power.

763
00:52:38,951 --> 00:52:41,787
I believe that

764
00:52:41,787 --> 00:52:44,957
great power should be used
toward great ends.

765
00:52:45,165 --> 00:52:47,501
Do you have questions
about the current world?

766
00:52:47,835 --> 00:52:50,254
In this world, to protect
the common order of the society,

767
00:52:50,254 --> 00:52:52,714
jujutsu sorcerers have to act in secret.

768
00:52:53,257 --> 00:52:54,633
In other words,

769
00:52:55,092 --> 00:52:57,594
this paradox is established

770
00:52:57,594 --> 00:53:00,639
due to that the strong
must adapt to the weak.

771
00:53:01,515 --> 00:53:03,767
It's so pitiful!

772
00:53:05,435 --> 00:53:10,023
We stopped our evolution by ourselves.

773
00:53:10,023 --> 00:53:11,358
Nonsense!

774
00:53:11,358 --> 00:53:15,362
It's time for mankind
to reconsider its strategy for survival!

775
00:53:15,737 --> 00:53:19,366
So we'd like you to help us.

776
00:53:19,950 --> 00:53:21,451
Help with what?

777
00:53:21,994 --> 00:53:24,246
Kill all non-sorcerers

778
00:53:24,246 --> 00:53:26,665
and create a world
with only jujutsu sorcerers.

779
00:53:28,083 --> 00:53:29,126
What

780
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:30,794
is he talking about?

781
00:53:33,005 --> 00:53:34,923
Could you stop preaching

782
00:53:34,923 --> 00:53:37,634
your crazy ideas to my students?

783
00:53:40,804 --> 00:53:43,140
Satoru! Long time no see!

784
00:53:43,348 --> 00:53:46,393
Get away from those kids, Suguru.

785
00:53:48,812 --> 00:53:51,815
I heard in this year's Grade 1,
there are outstanding students.

786
00:53:51,815 --> 00:53:53,025
Now I see.

787
00:53:53,025 --> 00:53:54,902
You are their teacher.

788
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,987
A Special Grade cursed human,

789
00:53:57,279 --> 00:53:59,114
a cursed corpse mutation,

790
00:53:59,281 --> 00:54:00,866
a descendant of cursed speech users,

791
00:54:01,241 --> 00:54:02,451
and

792
00:54:02,951 --> 00:54:05,662
the Zen'in clan's failure.

793
00:54:05,787 --> 00:54:07,164
You bastard!

794
00:54:07,164 --> 00:54:08,665
Watch your mouth.

795
00:54:09,124 --> 00:54:12,920
I don't need any monkeys
like you in my world.

796
00:54:16,757 --> 00:54:18,008
I'm sorry.

797
00:54:18,967 --> 00:54:21,845
I don't really understand
what you're talking about,

798
00:54:22,846 --> 00:54:23,847
but,

799
00:54:25,015 --> 00:54:28,602
I won't help anyone
who insults my friends!

800
00:54:31,021 --> 00:54:32,231
My apologies.

801
00:54:32,231 --> 00:54:34,483
I was not intending to upset you.

802
00:54:34,608 --> 00:54:37,945
Then what exactly did you come for?

803
00:54:39,530 --> 00:54:41,490
To declare war.

804
00:54:42,574 --> 00:54:44,743
Everyone here,

805
00:54:45,244 --> 00:54:48,288
open your ears and listen closely!

806
00:54:49,039 --> 00:54:52,960
On December 24th, when the sun sets,

807
00:54:52,960 --> 00:54:55,379
we will conduct
the Night Parade of a Hundred Demons.

808
00:54:56,505 --> 00:54:58,507
It will take place
in the crucible of curses,

809
00:54:59,007 --> 00:55:00,801
Shinjuku, Tokyo,

810
00:55:02,135 --> 00:55:05,389
and the holy land of jujutsu, Kyoto.

811
00:55:05,889 --> 00:55:08,392
We will unleash
thousands of curses in each place.

812
00:55:08,392 --> 00:55:11,311
Of course, their command
will be massacre.

813
00:55:12,020 --> 00:55:16,608
If you want to avoid a scene like hell,
come and stop it with all efforts.

814
00:55:17,651 --> 00:55:21,738
Let us curse each other freely!

815
00:55:28,161 --> 00:55:29,580
Mr. Geto!

816
00:55:29,580 --> 00:55:31,206
The store's closing!

817
00:55:31,206 --> 00:55:32,958
It's already that late?

818
00:55:33,417 --> 00:55:35,335
I'm sorry, Satoru.

819
00:55:35,502 --> 00:55:39,381
They insist on getting crepes
from Takeshita Street.

820
00:55:39,381 --> 00:55:41,258
Hurry!

821
00:55:41,258 --> 00:55:43,343
So I'm leaving now.

822
00:55:43,760 --> 00:55:46,889
I don't see what's so good
about a place with so many monkeys.

823
00:55:46,889 --> 00:55:49,057
Do you think we'll let you go?

824
00:55:50,809 --> 00:55:52,060
Just save it.

825
00:56:00,068 --> 00:56:02,571
Your precious students
are within my attacking range.

826
00:56:05,324 --> 00:56:07,659
Everyone, see you on the battlefield.

827
00:56:21,632 --> 00:56:23,383
Survival of the weakest.

828
00:56:23,967 --> 00:56:26,553
That's the proper form
the society should take.

829
00:56:27,304 --> 00:56:30,224
We should help the weak
and curb the violent.

830
00:56:30,432 --> 00:56:31,975
Listen, Satoru.

831
00:56:32,184 --> 00:56:34,978
Sorcerers are for
protecting non-sorcerers.

832
00:56:35,312 --> 00:56:37,147
That's your argument?

833
00:56:37,397 --> 00:56:39,733
I hate righteousness.

834
00:56:42,819 --> 00:56:46,240
Are you the strongest
because you're Gojo Satoru?

835
00:56:46,532 --> 00:56:49,326
Or are you Gojo Satoru
because you're the strongest?

836
00:56:49,409 --> 00:56:51,078
What are you trying to say?

837
00:56:51,537 --> 00:56:53,872
If I could become you,

838
00:56:53,872 --> 00:56:57,793
then wouldn't my foolish ideals
become reasonable possibilities?

839
00:57:01,129 --> 00:57:02,923
I've decided how to live my life.

840
00:57:03,131 --> 00:57:06,760
All I have to do is to do my best.

841
00:57:45,966 --> 00:57:47,426
Geto Suguru,

842
00:57:47,885 --> 00:57:51,138
a Special Grade curse user
who uses cursed spirit manipulation.

843
00:57:51,513 --> 00:57:56,643
He draws in and manipulates
naturally occurring, unbound curses.

844
00:57:57,186 --> 00:57:59,980
He established a religious group

845
00:57:59,980 --> 00:58:02,649
to collect curses from its followers.

846
00:58:03,483 --> 00:58:06,612
He carries some curses himself,

847
00:58:06,612 --> 00:58:11,617
and the number of curses reported
in recent years is declining.

848
00:58:12,826 --> 00:58:16,163
His claim to possess 2,000 curses
may not be a bluff.

849
00:58:16,330 --> 00:58:20,834
Even so, statistically, most of them
are only at Grade 2 or below.

850
00:58:20,834 --> 00:58:24,880
And there can't be
much more than 50 curse users.

851
00:58:25,088 --> 00:58:28,342
That's actually the scary part.

852
00:58:28,342 --> 00:58:31,428
I don't think he'd start a war
he couldn't win.

853
00:58:31,762 --> 00:58:33,222
GOD DAMN!

854
00:58:33,555 --> 00:58:35,891
Put out a call for aid to all alumni,
the three major clans,

855
00:58:35,891 --> 00:58:38,852
and even the Ainu Jujutsu Society.

856
00:58:39,394 --> 00:58:40,979
It's all-out war!

857
00:58:41,313 --> 00:58:46,485
This time, completely exorcise
that curse, Geto!

858
00:58:46,568 --> 00:58:50,239
That's what that dumb principal
is probably spouting right now.

859
00:58:52,324 --> 00:58:56,245
(December 24th, Day of the Night Parade
of a Hundred Demons)

860
00:59:00,832 --> 00:59:03,460
If we try hard to kill each other,

861
00:59:03,460 --> 00:59:07,464
our chance of success
would be about 30%.

862
00:59:12,261 --> 00:59:14,263
If the Jujutsu Society joins too,

863
00:59:14,263 --> 00:59:16,640
we'll barely have a 20% chance.

864
00:59:17,349 --> 00:59:22,980
There's only one way
to make that slim chance of victory

865
00:59:23,564 --> 00:59:25,482
jump to 99%.

866
00:59:26,358 --> 00:59:28,318
I kill Okkotsu Yuta

867
00:59:28,318 --> 00:59:32,364
and obtain the special grade
vengeful cursed spirit, Orimoto Rika.

868
00:59:33,574 --> 00:59:38,495
They still believe my bluff
from my old time in school.

869
00:59:38,954 --> 00:59:41,707
It doesn't matter
if the cursed spirit is bound.

870
00:59:41,707 --> 00:59:43,876
So long as I kill its master,

871
00:59:43,876 --> 00:59:46,879
I can absorb any curse I want.

872
00:59:48,338 --> 00:59:50,174
With such a high chance of victory,

873
00:59:50,174 --> 00:59:53,427
the school won't let Okkotsu to fight.

874
00:59:53,552 --> 00:59:54,887
After all, there's a chance

875
00:59:54,887 --> 00:59:57,264
both enemies and allies
could be wiped out.

876
00:59:58,098 --> 01:00:00,309
The real purpose of the Night Parade

877
01:00:00,309 --> 01:00:03,187
is to get Okkotsu
isolated and unprotected.

878
01:00:05,022 --> 01:00:06,023
Now,

879
01:00:06,481 --> 01:00:09,234
let's raise the curtain on a new age.

880
01:00:11,862 --> 01:00:13,488
It feels like

881
01:00:15,240 --> 01:00:17,743
something crazy is going to happen.

882
01:00:19,953 --> 01:00:21,288
Maki!

883
01:00:21,288 --> 01:00:24,458
What are you doing here?
Classes are canceled for the week.

884
01:00:24,458 --> 01:00:27,002
I just felt kinda restless.

885
01:00:27,920 --> 01:00:30,339
No one in the dorms, either.

886
01:00:30,672 --> 01:00:34,051
That's because Grade 2
were dispatched to Kyoto.

887
01:00:34,218 --> 01:00:37,221
Toge and Grade 3 and 4
are in Shinjuku as backup.

888
01:00:37,554 --> 01:00:40,098
The principal really likes Panda,

889
01:00:40,098 --> 01:00:41,934
so he's probably with Toge.

890
01:00:41,934 --> 01:00:42,809
I see.

891
01:00:48,190 --> 01:00:49,441
Just ask.

892
01:00:49,983 --> 01:00:51,485
You've been curious, right?

893
01:00:51,610 --> 01:00:53,946
About me being a failure.

894
01:00:54,363 --> 01:00:55,656
Well, no...

895
01:00:57,616 --> 01:00:58,534
yes.

896
01:01:01,745 --> 01:01:03,997
My family, the Zen'in clan,

897
01:01:03,997 --> 01:01:07,459
is one of the elite families of
jujutsu sorcerers, three major clans.

898
01:01:07,876 --> 01:01:12,172
Do you know the minimum requirement
for a jujutsu sorcerer?

899
01:01:12,923 --> 01:01:13,966
What is it?

900
01:01:16,510 --> 01:01:18,345
Able to see curses.

901
01:01:18,345 --> 01:01:19,471
I see.

902
01:01:20,222 --> 01:01:21,515
Ordinary people

903
01:01:21,515 --> 01:01:24,810
can see them in special circumstances,
like before death,

904
01:01:25,644 --> 01:01:28,981
but I can't see curses
without these lame glasses.

905
01:01:29,398 --> 01:01:32,860
The cursed tools I use
are already imbued with cursed energy.

906
01:01:32,860 --> 01:01:35,028
It doesn't come from me.

907
01:01:36,905 --> 01:01:39,324
But thanks to that,
I got out of that family.

908
01:01:39,741 --> 01:01:42,202
The food was awful, rooms were small,

909
01:01:42,202 --> 01:01:44,580
and with old and unknown men
running around.

910
01:01:44,580 --> 01:01:46,582
It seriously sucked!

911
01:01:48,792 --> 01:01:50,169
Don't call me by my last name.

912
01:01:50,627 --> 01:01:54,882
Not everyone is immune
to curses like you!

913
01:01:55,257 --> 01:01:57,676
Don't ask me about cursed energy.

914
01:02:01,263 --> 01:02:04,308
Why do you still want to
be a jujutsu sorcerer, then?

915
01:02:04,474 --> 01:02:07,019
Because I'm spiteful.

916
01:02:07,644 --> 01:02:11,231
I want to see them surprised
when I go back one day

917
01:02:11,815 --> 01:02:14,484
as a Grade 1 sorcerer
who can't see curses!

918
01:02:15,027 --> 01:02:18,447
Then I'll crush
the Zen'in clan from within!

919
01:02:22,492 --> 01:02:23,660
What?

920
01:02:23,869 --> 01:02:26,705
Well, I was just thinking
that's so like you.

921
01:02:28,165 --> 01:02:29,416
I wish

922
01:02:30,667 --> 01:02:32,377
I could be like you,

923
01:02:33,045 --> 01:02:35,547
so strong and unyielding.

924
01:02:43,472 --> 01:02:46,725
I wish I had never given birth to you.

925
01:02:47,267 --> 01:02:48,227
You're

926
01:02:48,519 --> 01:02:49,645
the shame of the Zen'in clan!

927
01:02:50,521 --> 01:02:51,688
Everyone,

928
01:02:52,689 --> 01:02:55,067
you don't want to turn out like Maki.

929
01:03:03,492 --> 01:03:06,620
If there's anything
I can help with, just tell me.

930
01:03:06,620 --> 01:03:09,998
Let's crush the Zen'in clan!
Or something like that.

931
01:03:13,293 --> 01:03:14,378
Moron.

932
01:03:14,419 --> 01:03:16,630
There's no point
if I don't do it by myself.

933
01:03:17,798 --> 01:03:19,258
I'm going back to my room.

934
01:03:19,800 --> 01:03:21,009
See you.

935
01:03:25,681 --> 01:03:27,558
Am I an idiot?

936
01:03:28,433 --> 01:03:30,853
Don't start thinking
this means you've been accepted!

937
01:03:32,855 --> 01:03:35,649
Emerge from darkness,
blacker than darkness.

938
01:03:35,732 --> 01:03:38,318
Purify the residuals, curses all gone.

939
01:03:45,993 --> 01:03:48,203
A Curtain was drawn over the school?

940
01:03:48,453 --> 01:03:50,205
But who and why?

941
01:03:56,587 --> 01:03:59,715
Avoid destroying buildings
and facilities as much as possible.

942
01:04:00,257 --> 01:04:02,926
There may be some civilians still here.

943
01:04:02,926 --> 01:04:05,220
If you find any, evacuate them.

944
01:04:05,429 --> 01:04:07,431
Are you listening, Satoru?

945
01:04:07,723 --> 01:04:08,724
There's one guy

946
01:04:09,099 --> 01:04:11,476
who may be a trouble.

947
01:04:12,394 --> 01:04:13,604
I see.

948
01:04:13,604 --> 01:04:15,355
That bandaged guy?

949
01:04:15,689 --> 01:04:18,942
Yes. We'll take on all the rest.

950
01:04:18,942 --> 01:04:20,444
I've said this many times, but...

951
01:04:20,444 --> 01:04:21,778
Got it.

952
01:04:21,778 --> 01:04:23,989
We're only here for stalling them.

953
01:04:23,989 --> 01:04:28,243
Let's have some fun
until Geto finishes his job.

954
01:04:29,203 --> 01:04:30,746
You're here too?

955
01:04:30,913 --> 01:04:32,456
Is that a problem?

956
01:04:32,789 --> 01:04:35,459
What the hell are you doing here?

957
01:04:37,294 --> 01:04:38,545
Sorry,

958
01:04:38,545 --> 01:04:40,631
but I don't have time
to chat with monkeys.

959
01:04:41,423 --> 01:04:42,424
Mr. Gojo!

960
01:04:42,925 --> 01:04:44,259
I have a report!

961
01:04:45,594 --> 01:04:47,221
What's the matter?

962
01:04:47,221 --> 01:04:48,430
Well...

963
01:04:48,889 --> 01:04:52,392
That showing off guy is not here,
on the front lines?

964
01:04:52,392 --> 01:04:54,061
Is he in Kyoto?

965
01:04:54,061 --> 01:04:56,480
If that's the case,
we should have received some info.

966
01:04:57,940 --> 01:05:00,067
It's nothing. What's up?

967
01:05:00,442 --> 01:05:02,486
I know this isn't the best time,

968
01:05:02,486 --> 01:05:04,238
but I think it's better
to speak up sooner.

969
01:05:04,488 --> 01:05:07,574
About the investigation into Okkotsu
that you previously requested...

970
01:05:12,079 --> 01:05:13,497
Panda! Toge!

971
01:05:14,248 --> 01:05:15,415
What is it?

972
01:05:15,541 --> 01:05:17,417
No questions!

973
01:05:17,417 --> 01:05:20,003
I'm sending you two
back to Jujutsu High right now!

974
01:05:21,547 --> 01:05:24,216
Geto is there now.

975
01:05:24,216 --> 01:05:26,301
I'm absolutely, probably, certain!

976
01:05:26,301 --> 01:05:27,761
Which is it?!

977
01:05:27,970 --> 01:05:29,471
If my intuition is right,

978
01:05:29,471 --> 01:05:31,682
in the worst case,
Yuta and Maki could both die!

979
01:05:32,891 --> 01:05:35,602
I'll go back there
after I take down that foreigner.

980
01:05:35,602 --> 01:05:37,062
Protect those two.

981
01:05:37,479 --> 01:05:38,730
Sorry, but defend them with your lives!

982
01:05:40,816 --> 01:05:41,942
-OK!
-Salmon!

983
01:05:45,696 --> 01:05:47,865
They figured it out?

984
01:05:47,865 --> 01:05:51,368
We should've prepared
a stand-in at least.

985
01:05:51,618 --> 01:05:53,662
A bad dummy would make things worse.

986
01:05:53,662 --> 01:05:55,789
That's what Mr. Geto said.

987
01:05:55,789 --> 01:05:57,124
Mimiko, Nanako!

988
01:05:57,541 --> 01:05:59,001
What is it?

989
01:05:59,001 --> 01:06:00,502
We're stepping up the plan.

990
01:06:00,502 --> 01:06:01,670
Engage.

991
01:06:05,257 --> 01:06:06,967
I've been waiting for this!

992
01:06:09,303 --> 01:06:13,140
I'm your opponent,

993
01:06:13,140 --> 01:06:14,224
Special Grade.

994
01:06:14,808 --> 01:06:16,310
Sorry,

995
01:06:17,186 --> 01:06:19,229
but I'm in a hurry right now.

996
01:06:23,442 --> 01:06:24,610
A Curtain's been drawn!

997
01:06:24,610 --> 01:06:26,612
Does that mean
Satoru's intuition was right?

998
01:06:26,612 --> 01:06:27,946
I'll break the Curtain!

999
01:06:27,946 --> 01:06:30,949
That's the shortcut.

1000
01:06:30,949 --> 01:06:32,034
Spiced cod roe!

1001
01:06:32,201 --> 01:06:33,577
Oh?

1002
01:06:35,245 --> 01:06:38,332
Someone made a hole in the Curtain.

1003
01:06:38,832 --> 01:06:41,752
Nothing ever goes quite as planned.

1004
01:06:42,836 --> 01:06:45,756
It will take them five minutes
to travel from the battlefield to here.

1005
01:06:46,340 --> 01:06:50,010
Should I ignore them,
or should I take care of them first?

1006
01:06:51,887 --> 01:06:53,639
So hard to decide.

1007
01:06:59,061 --> 01:07:02,397
Breaking through all the walls
to take a shortcut?

1008
01:07:03,273 --> 01:07:04,733
Not bad.

1009
01:07:04,733 --> 01:07:06,527
Take that!

1010
01:07:08,070 --> 01:07:08,779
Maki!

1011
01:07:10,280 --> 01:07:11,657
Focus.

1012
01:07:13,700 --> 01:07:16,203
This guy can handle close combat too?

1013
01:07:42,354 --> 01:07:43,856
Predictable.

1014
01:07:44,773 --> 01:07:46,108
Because it was a feint.

1015
01:07:47,442 --> 01:07:50,195
Unblockable Drumming Beat!

1016
01:08:10,007 --> 01:08:10,924
That was close.

1017
01:08:11,758 --> 01:08:13,427
Same to you.

1018
01:08:15,929 --> 01:08:17,681
Plummet!

1019
01:08:24,813 --> 01:08:27,149
Toge! You okay?

1020
01:08:27,524 --> 01:08:28,442
Salmon roe.

1021
01:08:28,734 --> 01:08:31,236
Yeah, Maki comes first.

1022
01:08:34,031 --> 01:08:36,950
Maki, are you okay? Maki?

1023
01:08:36,950 --> 01:08:38,327
Leaf mustard.

1024
01:08:39,203 --> 01:08:41,663
N-Not yet...

1025
01:08:53,217 --> 01:08:54,343
Another quake?

1026
01:08:54,927 --> 01:08:56,845
What's going on?

1027
01:08:59,097 --> 01:08:59,973
Wonderful.

1028
01:09:00,933 --> 01:09:02,518
Wonderful!

1029
01:09:02,851 --> 01:09:06,063
I am very touched right now!

1030
01:09:06,230 --> 01:09:09,024
You all raced here to save Okkotsu?

1031
01:09:09,024 --> 01:09:12,277
Jujutsu sorcerers are sacrificing
themselves for a fellow sorcerer!

1032
01:09:12,694 --> 01:09:14,780
Affection! Admiration!

1033
01:09:15,197 --> 01:09:17,032
The world I long for

1034
01:09:17,407 --> 01:09:19,618
is here before my eyes!

1035
01:09:27,000 --> 01:09:28,627
Maki?

1036
01:09:29,378 --> 01:09:30,963
To be honest,

1037
01:09:30,963 --> 01:09:33,882
I wanted you to live too, Okkotsu.

1038
01:09:34,591 --> 01:09:37,678
But this is all for the future
of the jujutsu world.

1039
01:09:38,387 --> 01:09:39,888
Panda...

1040
01:09:40,389 --> 01:09:42,307
Yuta...

1041
01:09:44,226 --> 01:09:46,353
Inumaki...

1042
01:09:46,562 --> 01:09:50,107
Run...

1043
01:09:52,484 --> 01:09:55,487
(Record: December 24th, 2017)

1044
01:09:56,071 --> 01:09:57,948
Come out, Rika!

1045
01:09:59,741 --> 01:10:01,410
(Special grade vengeful cursed spirit,
Orimoto Rika)

1046
01:10:01,410 --> 01:10:02,744
(Fully Manifested the Second Time)

1047
01:10:03,078 --> 01:10:04,746
I will kill you.

1048
01:10:05,080 --> 01:10:07,416
I'll kill you!

1049
01:10:21,054 --> 01:10:22,764
Quantity before quality.

1050
01:10:23,348 --> 01:10:25,767
What's your move, Queen of Curses?

1051
01:10:42,826 --> 01:10:43,952
Rika.

1052
01:10:47,956 --> 01:10:50,918
All heavily injured, especially Maki.

1053
01:10:53,045 --> 01:10:54,171
I won't let you die!

1054
01:11:02,638 --> 01:11:04,806
Not fair!

1055
01:11:04,806 --> 01:11:08,060
It's always you!

1056
01:11:08,060 --> 01:11:09,645
What are you doing, Rika?

1057
01:11:10,521 --> 01:11:12,523
She saved my life.

1058
01:11:12,856 --> 01:11:16,485
Handle her with more care
than a butterfly or a flower!

1059
01:11:19,404 --> 01:11:22,074
I'm sorry!

1060
01:11:22,449 --> 01:11:24,076
Don't be mad.

1061
01:11:24,076 --> 01:11:25,077
I'm not mad.

1062
01:11:25,077 --> 01:11:27,412
Don't hate me.

1063
01:11:27,412 --> 01:11:29,081
I don't hate you.

1064
01:11:31,041 --> 01:11:33,085
Our enemy is that man there.

1065
01:11:33,418 --> 01:11:36,046
Yuta, do you hate him?

1066
01:11:36,046 --> 01:11:37,589
Yeah, very much.

1067
01:11:38,799 --> 01:11:41,635
Then I hate him too!

1068
01:11:41,635 --> 01:11:42,594
Welcome back.

1069
01:11:44,805 --> 01:11:46,849
Why did you stop attacking?

1070
01:11:46,849 --> 01:11:51,103
Healing with cursed energy requires
an advanced Reverse Cursed Technique.

1071
01:11:51,687 --> 01:11:56,859
It's better to pay
some of your attention over there.

1072
01:11:58,026 --> 01:12:00,404
Now, shall we continue?

1073
01:12:01,780 --> 01:12:03,824
Rika, let's use that.

1074
01:12:06,910 --> 01:12:08,704
Snake Eyes and Fangs?

1075
01:12:08,704 --> 01:12:09,705
Those are...

1076
01:12:09,955 --> 01:12:11,748
The cursed seals of the Inumaki clan!

1077
01:12:21,717 --> 01:12:23,093
Die.

1078
01:12:30,517 --> 01:12:31,977
Wonderful!

1079
01:12:32,394 --> 01:12:35,314
Cursed speech is a powerful technique
passed down in the Inumaki clan.

1080
01:12:35,689 --> 01:12:40,194
Yet this young man made it
with less than a year of studying!

1081
01:12:40,402 --> 01:12:42,362
That really is hard to use.

1082
01:12:42,738 --> 01:12:45,657
The cursed energy scatters,
and it's hard to aim.

1083
01:12:45,657 --> 01:12:47,701
Inumakin is incredible.

1084
01:12:48,493 --> 01:12:52,456
So Orimoto Rika's true form
is ever-changing.

1085
01:12:52,456 --> 01:12:54,708
She's an endless bundle
of cursed energy.

1086
01:12:55,042 --> 01:12:58,629
Yes. My friends are amazing.

1087
01:12:58,629 --> 01:13:02,090
And you! You!

1088
01:13:02,090 --> 01:13:04,384
I want her even more.

1089
01:13:06,136 --> 01:13:08,096
I'll beat you to a pulp!

1090
01:13:38,585 --> 01:13:41,505
Why is Mr. Nanami in Kyoto?

1091
01:13:41,505 --> 01:13:43,048
I wanted him to see me shine!

1092
01:13:43,048 --> 01:13:44,132
Shut up!

1093
01:13:44,591 --> 01:13:46,969
Quit griping and fight!

1094
01:13:47,553 --> 01:13:49,054
There are still more coming!

1095
01:13:51,390 --> 01:13:53,392
Troublesome.

1096
01:14:14,705 --> 01:14:16,164
That makes fifty.

1097
01:14:16,498 --> 01:14:18,834
I've cleared the numbers
required for the incentive.

1098
01:14:18,834 --> 01:14:23,630
Now it's time to work a little more
for full bonus.

1099
01:14:27,968 --> 01:14:29,636
How old are you two?

1100
01:14:30,262 --> 01:14:31,847
Fifteen.

1101
01:14:31,847 --> 01:14:33,765
Still minors.

1102
01:14:34,224 --> 01:14:36,393
It's not too late for you to turn back.

1103
01:14:36,810 --> 01:14:39,396
You can't tell right from wrong now.

1104
01:14:40,105 --> 01:14:41,481
Annoying!

1105
01:14:41,481 --> 01:14:44,026
Mimiko, doesn't he totally piss you off?

1106
01:14:44,026 --> 01:14:45,903
Shall we hang him, Nanako?

1107
01:14:46,403 --> 01:14:48,906
You don't know, do you?

1108
01:14:49,573 --> 01:14:52,826
How jujutsu sorcerers will be treated

1109
01:14:52,826 --> 01:14:55,913
in such rural places
that aren't even on maps?

1110
01:14:56,830 --> 01:15:01,585
Right or wrong?
That's your call to decide.

1111
01:15:02,961 --> 01:15:04,963
As long as Mr. Geto says it,

1112
01:15:05,172 --> 01:15:06,757
black can be white,

1113
01:15:06,757 --> 01:15:08,634
and white can be black.

1114
01:15:11,637 --> 01:15:16,642
We believe in the world he envisioned.

1115
01:15:18,018 --> 01:15:19,520
Anyone who gets in his way,

1116
01:15:19,853 --> 01:15:21,396
we'll hang them!

1117
01:15:25,692 --> 01:15:28,028
Miguel, what are you doing?

1118
01:15:28,028 --> 01:15:29,947
Look for yourself.

1119
01:15:30,030 --> 01:15:31,698
So tenacious.

1120
01:15:36,036 --> 01:15:39,581
That rope... It has an unusual curse
woven into it.

1121
01:15:40,374 --> 01:15:42,584
It's disrupting my techniques.

1122
01:15:43,001 --> 01:15:45,838
I barely have half left.

1123
01:15:45,838 --> 01:15:49,675
Do you know how many decades it took

1124
01:15:49,675 --> 01:15:52,344
the sorcerers in my country
to weave this one rope?

1125
01:15:52,553 --> 01:15:53,887
I don't care.

1126
01:15:53,887 --> 01:15:55,848
My time is much

1127
01:15:56,098 --> 01:15:57,641
more precious than that.

1128
01:15:58,684 --> 01:16:00,060
Out of my way.

1129
01:16:06,233 --> 01:16:08,360
Not good! Mr. Gojo's pissed off!

1130
01:16:08,652 --> 01:16:12,573
So this is Limitless cursed technique
Geto mentioned.

1131
01:16:12,573 --> 01:16:14,867
It interferes items on the atomic level,

1132
01:16:14,867 --> 01:16:19,872
using precise manipulation of
cursed energy to control space and time.

1133
01:16:19,997 --> 01:16:23,375
What makes that all possible
is the power of those eyes?

1134
01:16:23,917 --> 01:16:26,295
Still more than 12 minutes left.

1135
01:16:26,295 --> 01:16:28,380
I have to hold on with my life!

1136
01:17:36,532 --> 01:17:38,492
That was close.

1137
01:17:38,492 --> 01:17:40,369
I'll focus on hit-and-run.

1138
01:17:40,536 --> 01:17:43,789
I'll give everything I've got
to endure these last ten minutes.

1139
01:17:43,789 --> 01:17:46,375
If I die, I'm cursing you, Geto!

1140
01:17:51,046 --> 01:17:53,006
Ms. Ieri, please look after
this one too.

1141
01:17:53,966 --> 01:17:55,342
Set him down over there.

1142
01:17:55,342 --> 01:17:56,176
Yes!

1143
01:17:56,176 --> 01:17:58,345
What are you doing?

1144
01:17:58,345 --> 01:18:02,140
It's all right. Mr. Ieri will cure you.

1145
01:18:04,142 --> 01:18:05,727
Counting on you!

1146
01:18:07,312 --> 01:18:07,980
Sheesh.

1147
01:18:08,522 --> 01:18:12,484
You really made
so much trouble for us, Geto.

1148
01:18:14,653 --> 01:18:17,155
It's your first time
experiencing such violent emotion,

1149
01:18:17,155 --> 01:18:19,616
and cursed energy
is filling your body, isn't it?

1150
01:18:20,117 --> 01:18:23,453
Heightening of physical prowess,
sense of omnipotence...

1151
01:18:23,453 --> 01:18:25,747
Your senses must be sharpened too.

1152
01:18:26,206 --> 01:18:29,459
The riff-raff are no match for you now.

1153
01:18:29,459 --> 01:18:31,211
I'll have to crush you myself.

1154
01:18:33,130 --> 01:18:34,965
Follow my lead, Rika.

1155
01:18:35,549 --> 01:18:38,468
Mankind stands
at the top of the food chain,

1156
01:18:39,178 --> 01:18:41,638
yet they imagined
the existence of higher beings

1157
01:18:41,638 --> 01:18:42,973
and called them gods.

1158
01:18:43,348 --> 01:18:45,642
Don't you find it strange?

1159
01:18:45,642 --> 01:18:49,855
Especially when
we jujutsu sorcerers exist.

1160
01:19:41,865 --> 01:19:47,371
In the end, monkeys just want to ignore
the existence of better beings.

1161
01:19:47,913 --> 01:19:51,750
Don't say childish crap
like you want to be a god!

1162
01:19:52,125 --> 01:19:55,504
You're missing the point, Okkotsu.

1163
01:20:10,978 --> 01:20:13,814
What I long for isn't enlightenment,

1164
01:20:13,814 --> 01:20:15,274
but the chosen people.

1165
01:20:15,607 --> 01:20:21,196
Due to sheer numbers,
the weak could smash the strong.

1166
01:20:21,196 --> 01:20:25,701
The audacity of the monkeys who do that

1167
01:20:25,701 --> 01:20:27,953
makes me so sick.

1168
01:20:29,037 --> 01:20:30,664
Yuta...

1169
01:20:31,290 --> 01:20:33,667
It's all right. I'm used to it now.

1170
01:20:33,917 --> 01:20:36,003
Are we done debating?

1171
01:20:48,223 --> 01:20:49,641
He's even faster!

1172
01:20:58,567 --> 01:21:00,110
You shouldn't have done that.

1173
01:21:00,110 --> 01:21:02,070
When you imbue the curse too abruptly,

1174
01:21:02,070 --> 01:21:03,697
the vessel won't last.

1175
01:21:03,822 --> 01:21:06,241
Didn't Satoru teach you that?

1176
01:21:06,241 --> 01:21:07,576
You imbue curses bit by...

1177
01:21:20,088 --> 01:21:21,882
You're not bad.

1178
01:21:22,508 --> 01:21:23,634
I don't get it!

1179
01:21:24,635 --> 01:21:27,137
I don't know about any sorcerers
outside of this school,

1180
01:21:27,763 --> 01:21:29,640
so I don't know

1181
01:21:30,140 --> 01:21:31,892
if you're right or not!

1182
01:21:32,351 --> 01:21:33,852
But...

1183
01:21:34,144 --> 01:21:36,355
in order to remain with all my friends,

1184
01:21:37,189 --> 01:21:41,443
in order for me to believe
it's okay that I'm alive,

1185
01:21:42,402 --> 01:21:45,614
I have to kill you!

1186
01:21:46,198 --> 01:21:48,408
You're egotistical.

1187
01:21:48,408 --> 01:21:50,953
Still, self-affirmation, huh?

1188
01:21:51,119 --> 01:21:55,666
There's probably nothing
more important than that.

1189
01:21:56,375 --> 01:22:00,254
In that case, I'll also use
my full force to kill you.

1190
01:22:00,254 --> 01:22:02,881
I won't compromise on
quality or quantity anymore.

1191
01:22:03,257 --> 01:22:04,883
Do you know

1192
01:22:04,883 --> 01:22:07,344
there are only four people
crowned Special Grade?

1193
01:22:07,845 --> 01:22:10,389
But there are 16 curses.

1194
01:22:10,722 --> 01:22:12,850
This is one of them.

1195
01:22:13,433 --> 01:22:15,853
Special grade potential spirit,

1196
01:22:16,520 --> 01:22:18,856
Tamamo-no-mae!

1197
01:22:19,439 --> 01:22:25,362
On top of that, I'll combine
the 4,461 curses I possess into one,

1198
01:22:25,821 --> 01:22:27,364
and strike you with it.

1199
01:22:29,950 --> 01:22:33,120
Cursed Spirit Manipulation, Supreme Art:

1200
01:22:38,083 --> 01:22:40,002
Maelstrom.

1201
01:23:09,948 --> 01:23:11,033
Mr. Nanami.

1202
01:23:13,243 --> 01:23:14,995
I'll take care of it.

1203
01:24:06,964 --> 01:24:09,091
New Shadow Style, Simple Domain!

1204
01:24:09,091 --> 01:24:10,300
Quick Draw!

1205
01:24:18,517 --> 01:24:20,394
Don't let up, Miwa!

1206
01:24:21,728 --> 01:24:23,230
Mechamaru, above!

1207
01:24:27,568 --> 01:24:28,986
You too.

1208
01:24:29,987 --> 01:24:31,989
Everyone, stay alert.

1209
01:24:33,532 --> 01:24:34,491
Kamo.

1210
01:24:34,783 --> 01:24:37,286
Seven cursed spirits at two o'clock.

1211
01:24:37,286 --> 01:24:39,955
Roger that. Where did Todo go?

1212
01:24:41,707 --> 01:24:43,458
I think you'll see him soon.

1213
01:24:51,592 --> 01:24:53,760
Where have you been all this time, Todo?

1214
01:24:57,723 --> 01:24:59,266
What is that cursed energy?

1215
01:25:01,518 --> 01:25:03,145
That one's dangerous, Todo!

1216
01:25:03,145 --> 01:25:04,354
Don't rush in on your own!

1217
01:25:04,354 --> 01:25:06,690
-Wait for backup...
-Starting at eight, the talk show's

1218
01:25:06,690 --> 01:25:08,734
Christmas live special will be

1219
01:25:09,151 --> 01:25:11,236
hosting Takada!

1220
01:25:12,654 --> 01:25:15,490
I can't keep wasting any time here!

1221
01:25:15,908 --> 01:25:17,075
Todo!

1222
01:25:17,075 --> 01:25:17,993
Kamo.

1223
01:25:18,368 --> 01:25:21,997
Another ten or more cursed spirits
are approaching at six o'clock.

1224
01:25:23,207 --> 01:25:25,209
Everyone, prepare to intercept them!

1225
01:25:26,376 --> 01:25:28,629
There's no end to them.

1226
01:25:28,629 --> 01:25:30,214
When will this be over?

1227
01:25:34,009 --> 01:25:35,135
Okkotsu.

1228
01:25:35,636 --> 01:25:40,307
I'm truly glad I came to kill you
before you could fully wield

1229
01:25:40,766 --> 01:25:43,185
Orimoto Rika.

1230
01:25:50,359 --> 01:25:51,985
It's a promise.

1231
01:25:52,152 --> 01:25:55,531
When we grow up, we'll get married.

1232
01:25:56,031 --> 01:25:57,199
Sure.

1233
01:25:57,824 --> 01:26:03,580
Then we'll be together forever and ever!

1234
01:26:10,295 --> 01:26:11,255
Rika.

1235
01:26:11,255 --> 01:26:12,923
Yes?

1236
01:26:12,923 --> 01:26:15,300
Thank you for always protecting me.

1237
01:26:15,801 --> 01:26:18,470
Thank you for falling in love with me.

1238
01:26:19,096 --> 01:26:22,683
Could you lend me your power
one last time?

1239
01:26:24,434 --> 01:26:26,562
I want to stop him.

1240
01:26:26,895 --> 01:26:30,065
I don't need anything else after that.

1241
01:26:30,649 --> 01:26:36,530
I'll give you my future,
my heart, my body, everything.

1242
01:26:37,406 --> 01:26:40,993
From now on,
we'll truly be together forever.

1243
01:26:43,704 --> 01:26:46,290
I love you, Rika.

1244
01:26:47,958 --> 01:26:49,585
Shall we die together?

1245
01:26:58,051 --> 01:27:00,470
Yuta!

1246
01:27:00,888 --> 01:27:04,308
I love, love, love you!

1247
01:27:04,975 --> 01:27:09,062
He's offering himself as a sacrifice to
release the limit on her cursed energy?

1248
01:27:10,522 --> 01:27:13,317
So that's how you want it, womanizer?!

1249
01:27:13,984 --> 01:27:15,652
That's rude.

1250
01:27:16,695 --> 01:27:18,155
It's pure love.

1251
01:27:18,906 --> 01:27:21,575
Then I fight for justice!

1252
01:28:08,539 --> 01:28:10,415
Wonderful!

1253
01:28:11,416 --> 01:28:14,253
Absolutely wonderful!

1254
01:28:14,253 --> 01:28:17,172
Truly the power to change the world!

1255
01:28:17,840 --> 01:28:19,716
If I had Rika,

1256
01:28:19,716 --> 01:28:22,678
there would be no need
to sneak around gathering curses.

1257
01:28:23,428 --> 01:28:27,891
Next time... Next time, I'll obtain her!

1258
01:28:33,438 --> 01:28:35,440
You're late,

1259
01:28:36,066 --> 01:28:37,317
Satoru.

1260
01:28:38,777 --> 01:28:40,946
I didn't expect I will lose to you.

1261
01:28:41,488 --> 01:28:43,699
Is my family safe?

1262
01:28:44,074 --> 01:28:46,785
Every one of them managed to escape.

1263
01:28:47,244 --> 01:28:49,705
The ones in Kyoto
were under your orders too?

1264
01:28:50,664 --> 01:28:52,207
Yeah.

1265
01:28:52,666 --> 01:28:55,711
Unlike you, I'm a kind man.

1266
01:28:56,336 --> 01:29:00,340
You sent those two to let me defeat them

1267
01:29:00,632 --> 01:29:02,718
and set Okkotsu off, right?

1268
01:29:02,885 --> 01:29:04,845
I trust you.

1269
01:29:05,220 --> 01:29:07,431
A man with principles like you

1270
01:29:07,431 --> 01:29:10,517
wouldn't kill young sorcerers
without a reason.

1271
01:29:11,435 --> 01:29:13,312
Trust?

1272
01:29:17,608 --> 01:29:22,779
I didn't think
I still had any of that left.

1273
01:29:25,324 --> 01:29:27,618
Return this for me, will you?

1274
01:29:29,620 --> 01:29:32,372
Was the elementary school
your doing too?

1275
01:29:32,831 --> 01:29:34,124
Yeah.

1276
01:29:34,249 --> 01:29:35,876
I can't believe it.

1277
01:29:37,503 --> 01:29:40,172
Do you have any last words?

1278
01:29:41,048 --> 01:29:43,342
No matter what others say,

1279
01:29:43,926 --> 01:29:46,136
I hate those monkeys.

1280
01:29:47,763 --> 01:29:52,142
But I never held any hatred
for those in Jujutsu High.

1281
01:29:52,726 --> 01:29:58,398
I just couldn't wear
a heartfelt smile in this world.

1282
01:30:00,859 --> 01:30:02,069
Suguru.

1283
01:30:21,630 --> 01:30:25,551
At least hit me
with some curses at my end.

1284
01:30:42,985 --> 01:30:46,196
Yuta!

1285
01:30:47,865 --> 01:30:50,075
Yuta! Are you okay?

1286
01:30:50,075 --> 01:30:50,951
Leaf mustard.

1287
01:30:50,951 --> 01:30:53,996
Wake up, Yuta!

1288
01:30:55,455 --> 01:30:57,457
He's awake.

1289
01:30:59,334 --> 01:31:00,085
Everyone...

1290
01:31:00,460 --> 01:31:02,171
Your injuries... Maki.

1291
01:31:02,421 --> 01:31:03,630
Inumaki.

1292
01:31:03,839 --> 01:31:06,425
Wait! Panda, your arm isn't healed!

1293
01:31:06,425 --> 01:31:07,801
Chill out.

1294
01:31:07,926 --> 01:31:09,970
We're all doing better
than you are right now.

1295
01:31:10,304 --> 01:31:12,639
Unlike these other two,

1296
01:31:12,639 --> 01:31:14,224
my arm can be fixed later.

1297
01:31:14,808 --> 01:31:16,727
Thanks for saving us.

1298
01:31:17,102 --> 01:31:18,228
Salmon.

1299
01:31:19,771 --> 01:31:21,231
Yuta...

1300
01:31:29,323 --> 01:31:30,741
Sorry, Rika.

1301
01:31:31,158 --> 01:31:32,576
I've kept you waiting.

1302
01:31:32,743 --> 01:31:35,204
What's the matter, Yuta?

1303
01:31:36,288 --> 01:31:37,831
Well...

1304
01:31:38,749 --> 01:31:41,084
In exchange for her power,

1305
01:31:41,084 --> 01:31:43,879
I promised to go with Rika.

1306
01:31:43,879 --> 01:31:47,299
Don't you know that means dying?

1307
01:31:47,299 --> 01:31:48,634
What were you thinking, you idiot?

1308
01:31:48,634 --> 01:31:50,594
Well, I...

1309
01:31:55,432 --> 01:31:56,808
Rika?

1310
01:31:58,810 --> 01:32:00,020
Congratulations.

1311
01:32:00,437 --> 01:32:02,022
You managed to break the curse.

1312
01:32:02,147 --> 01:32:03,273
Who are you?

1313
01:32:03,273 --> 01:32:06,360
Your good-looking teacher, Gojo Satoru!

1314
01:32:07,528 --> 01:32:10,906
I thought the theory Yuta
came up with sounded interesting,

1315
01:32:11,740 --> 01:32:13,784
so I requested an investigation
into your families.

1316
01:32:14,493 --> 01:32:18,038
The investigation into Rika
was finished quite a long time ago,

1317
01:32:18,288 --> 01:32:20,958
but Yuta's was full of loopholes.

1318
01:32:21,708 --> 01:32:23,544
But later it came to light.

1319
01:32:24,628 --> 01:32:27,464
You're the descendant
of Sugawara Michizane!

1320
01:32:27,464 --> 01:32:29,758
That makes us super distant relatives!

1321
01:32:29,758 --> 01:32:31,009
Suga?!

1322
01:32:31,009 --> 01:32:31,844
Who?

1323
01:32:31,844 --> 01:32:33,846
One of Japan's three great spirits!

1324
01:32:33,846 --> 01:32:35,806
He's a super bigshot sorcerer.

1325
01:32:35,806 --> 01:32:36,473
Tuna.

1326
01:32:36,932 --> 01:32:38,475
You were right, Yuta.

1327
01:32:39,142 --> 01:32:41,562
Rika didn't place a curse on you.

1328
01:32:42,312 --> 01:32:45,148
You placed a curse on Rika.

1329
01:32:48,735 --> 01:32:49,987
Rika...

1330
01:32:50,112 --> 01:32:52,406
What do I do? Is she dying?
I have to save her!

1331
01:32:52,406 --> 01:32:56,869
Don't die! Don't die!

1332
01:32:59,121 --> 01:33:00,372
That's right.

1333
01:33:00,789 --> 01:33:04,877
Back then, I rejected
to accept Rika's death.

1334
01:33:05,460 --> 01:33:09,173
Now the one who placed the curse
has canceled the bond.

1335
01:33:10,174 --> 01:33:13,927
So long as the one who was cursed
doesn't seek any penalty,

1336
01:33:14,178 --> 01:33:15,512
it's fully broken now.

1337
01:33:15,971 --> 01:33:19,850
Of course, that was obvious
seeing her in that form.

1338
01:33:21,935 --> 01:33:24,771
It was all my fault.

1339
01:33:25,647 --> 01:33:27,774
I turned you into that.

1340
01:33:28,108 --> 01:33:30,611
I hurt all those people.

1341
01:33:30,611 --> 01:33:34,406
And I nearly caused everyone
to die when Geto came after me!

1342
01:33:35,032 --> 01:33:36,200
It's all...

1343
01:33:36,783 --> 01:33:39,328
It's all my...

1344
01:33:42,331 --> 01:33:45,167
Yuta, thank you

1345
01:33:45,626 --> 01:33:49,421
for giving me more time,
and letting me stay by your side.

1346
01:33:50,005 --> 01:33:52,049
During the past six years,

1347
01:33:52,049 --> 01:33:54,801
I've been happier
than I ever was while alive.

1348
01:34:08,106 --> 01:34:10,817
Bye-bye. Take care.

1349
01:34:13,445 --> 01:34:15,822
And don't come over here too soon, okay?

1350
01:34:17,115 --> 01:34:18,158
Okay.

1351
01:34:18,158 --> 01:34:19,493
See you later.

1352
01:34:56,280 --> 01:34:57,781
It's a bit late now,

1353
01:34:57,781 --> 01:35:00,284
but it was not your fault
with the incident of Geto.

1354
01:35:00,576 --> 01:35:04,079
He would've come to Jujutsu High
whether you were there or not.

1355
01:35:04,079 --> 01:35:05,497
You think so?

1356
01:35:05,497 --> 01:35:07,040
Also, here.

1357
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:08,542
My student ID.

1358
01:35:08,542 --> 01:35:10,169
You found it for me, Teacher?

1359
01:35:11,753 --> 01:35:14,673
No, not me.

1360
01:35:15,424 --> 01:35:17,134
My best friend.

1361
01:35:17,885 --> 01:35:19,678
The only one I had.

1362
01:35:21,430 --> 01:35:24,683
Yuta! How long are you gonna
keep us waiting?

1363
01:35:25,559 --> 01:35:26,685
Let's go!

1364
01:35:33,692 --> 01:35:34,943
OK!

1365
01:35:36,195 --> 01:35:44,703
"JUJUTSU KAISEN: ZERO"

1366
01:44:02,659 --> 01:44:04,119
This is good.

1367
01:44:04,119 --> 01:44:06,163
Isn't it?

1368
01:44:06,163 --> 01:44:08,707
I used a spice called Royco.

1369
01:44:08,707 --> 01:44:11,793
That gives it a good flavor.

1370
01:44:13,504 --> 01:44:18,509
Royco is a magic powder
making everything taste Kenyan.

1371
01:44:18,800 --> 01:44:22,012
Well, that guy really went back, right?

1372
01:44:24,014 --> 01:44:25,766
Good, then.

1373
01:44:26,266 --> 01:44:28,227
This really is good.

1374
01:44:28,227 --> 01:44:29,311
It's like nikujaga.

1375
01:44:29,311 --> 01:44:30,729
Nikujaga?

1376
01:44:30,729 --> 01:44:34,066
Call it beef stew. Beef stew!

1377
01:44:36,985 --> 01:44:38,278
What's wrong?

1378
01:44:38,904 --> 01:44:41,782
What are you doing here?

1379
01:44:42,783 --> 01:44:43,784
Huh?

1380
01:44:44,493 --> 01:44:45,953
Teacher?

1381
01:44:47,120 --> 01:44:48,580
Long time no see.
